  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Command to Leave Horeb'
      title: The Command to Leave Horeb
      number: 1
      content: '  These are the words that Moses spoke to all Israel beyond the Jordan
        in the wilderness, in the Arabah opposite Suph, between Paran and Tophel,
        Laban, Hazeroth, and Dizahab. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "It is eleven days\u2019 journey from Horeb by the way of Mount Seir
        to Kadesh-barnea. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'In the fortieth year, on the first day of the eleventh month, Moses
        spoke to the people of Israel according to all that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had given him in commandment to them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'after he had defeated Sihon the king of the Amorites, who lived in
        Heshbon, and Og the king of Bashan, who lived in Ashtaroth and in Edrei. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Beyond the Jordan, in the land of Moab, Moses undertook to explain
        this law, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God said to us in Horeb,
        \u2018You have stayed long enough at this mountain. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Turn and take your journey, and go to the hill country of the Amorites
        and to all their neighbors in the Arabah, in the hill country and in the
        lowland and in the Negeb and by the seacoast, the land of the Canaanites,
        and Lebanon, as far as the great river, the river Euphrates. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Leaders Appointed'
      title: Leaders Appointed
      number: 8
      content: "See, I have set the land before you. Go in and take possession of
        the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> swore to your fathers, to Abraham,
        to Isaac, and to Jacob, to give to them and to their offspring after them.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CAt that time I said to you, \u2018I am not able to bear you
        by myself. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has multiplied you, and
        behold, you are today as numerous as the stars of heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'May the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of your fathers, make
        you a thousand times as many as you are and bless you, as he has promised
        you! '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'How can I bear by myself the weight and burden of you and your strife? '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Choose for your tribes wise, understanding, and experienced men,
        and I will appoint them as your heads.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And you answered me, \u2018The thing that you have spoken is good
        for us to do.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So I took the heads of your tribes, wise and experienced men, and
        set them as heads over you, commanders of thousands, commanders of hundreds,
        commanders of fifties, commanders of tens, and officers, throughout your
        tribes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And I charged your judges at that time, \u2018Hear the cases between
        your brothers, and judge righteously between a man and his brother or the
        alien who is with him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "You shall not be partial in judgment. You shall hear the small and
        the great alike. You shall not be intimidated by anyone, for the judgment
        is God\u2019s. And the case that is too hard for you, you shall bring to
        me, and I will hear it.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: "18: Israel\u2019s Refusal to Enter the Land"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Refusal to Enter the Land"
      number: 18
      content: 'And I commanded you at that time all the things that you should do.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CThen we set out from Horeb and went through all that great
        and terrifying wilderness that you saw, on the way to the hill country of
        the Amorites, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God commanded us. And
        we came to Kadesh-barnea. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And I said to you, \u2018You have come to the hill country of the
        Amorites, which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God is giving us. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "See, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has set the land before
        you. Go up, take possession, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God
        of your fathers, has told you. Do not fear or be dismayed.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then all of you came near me and said, \u2018Let us send men before
        us, that they may explore the land for us and bring us word again of the
        way by which we must go up and the cities into which we shall come.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The thing seemed good to me, and I took twelve men from you, one
        man from each tribe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And they turned and went up into the hill country, and came to the
        Valley of Eshcol and spied it out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And they took in their hands some of the fruit of the land and brought
        it down to us, and brought us word again and said, \u2018It is a good land
        that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God is giving us.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CYet you would not go up, but rebelled against the command of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And you murmured in your tents and said, \u2018Because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        hated us he has brought us out of the land of Egypt, to give us into the
        hand of the Amorites, to destroy us. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Where are we going up? Our brothers have made our hearts melt, saying,
        \u201CThe people are greater and taller than we. The cities are great and
        fortified up to heaven. And besides, we have seen the sons of the Anakim
        there.\u201D\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then I said to you, \u2018Do not be in dread or afraid of them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God who goes before you will
        himself fight for you, just as he did for you in Egypt before your eyes, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "and in the wilderness, where you have seen how the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God carried you, as a man carries his son, all the way that you went
        until you came to this place.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Yet in spite of this word you did not believe the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, '
      comments: []
    - name: "33: The Penalty for Israel\u2019s Rebellion"
      title: "The Penalty for Israel\u2019s Rebellion"
      number: 33
      content: 'who went before you in the way to seek you out a place to pitch your
        tents, in fire by night and in the cloud by day, to show you by what way
        you should go.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "\u201CAnd the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> heard your words and was
        angered, and he swore, "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "\u2018Not one of these men of this evil generation shall see the
        good land that I swore to give to your fathers, "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "except Caleb the son of Jephunneh. He shall see it, and to him and
        to his children I will give the land on which he has trodden, because he
        has wholly followed the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Even with me the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was angry on your account
        and said, \u2018You also shall not go in there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Joshua the son of Nun, who stands before you, he shall enter. Encourage
        him, for he shall cause Israel to inherit it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And as for your little ones, who you said would become a prey, and
        your children, who today have no knowledge of good or evil, they shall go
        in there. And to them I will give it, and they shall possess it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "But as for you, turn, and journey into the wilderness in the direction
        of the Red Sea.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "\u201CThen you answered me, \u2018We have sinned against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        We ourselves will go up and fight, just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God commanded us.\u2019 And every one of you fastened on his weapons
        of war and thought it easy to go up into the hill country. "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u2018Say to them,
        Do not go up or fight, for I am not in your midst, lest you be defeated before
        your enemies.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'So I spoke to you, and you would not listen; but you rebelled against
        the command of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and presumptuously went up
        into the hill country. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Then the Amorites who lived in that hill country came out against
        you and chased you as bees do and beat you down in Seir as far as Hormah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'And you returned and wept before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        but the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> did not listen to your voice or give
        ear to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: So you remained at Kadesh many days, the days that you remained there.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Wilderness Years'
      title: The Wilderness Years
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CThen we turned and journeyed into the wilderness in the direction
        of the Red Sea, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> told me. And for many
        days we traveled around Mount Seir. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u2018You have been traveling around this mountain country long enough.
        Turn northward "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "and command the people, \u201CYou are about to pass through the territory
        of your brothers, the people of Esau, who live in Seir; and they will be
        afraid of you. So be very careful. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Do not contend with them, for I will not give you any of their land,
        no, not so much as for the sole of the foot to tread on, because I have given
        Mount Seir to Esau as a possession. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You shall purchase food from them with money, that you may eat, and
        you shall also buy water from them with money, that you may drink. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has blessed you in all
        the work of your hands. He knows your going through this great wilderness.
        These forty years the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has been with
        you. You have lacked nothing.\u201D\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So we went on, away from our brothers, the people of Esau, who live
        in Seir, away from the Arabah road from Elath and Ezion-geber.\u201CAnd we
        turned and went in the direction of the wilderness of Moab. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u2018Do not harass
        Moab or contend with them in battle, for I will not give you any of their
        land for a possession, because I have given Ar to the people of Lot for a
        possession.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '(The Emim formerly lived there, a people great and many, and tall
        as the Anakim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Like the Anakim they are also counted as Rephaim, but the Moabites
        call them Emim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The Horites also lived in Seir formerly, but the people of Esau dispossessed
        them and destroyed them from before them and settled in their place, as Israel
        did to the land of their possession, which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        gave to them.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u2018Now rise up and go over the brook Zered.\u2019 So we went over
        the brook Zered. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And the time from our leaving Kadesh-barnea until we crossed the
        brook Zered was thirty-eight years, until the entire generation, that is,
        the men of war, had perished from the camp, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had sworn to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For indeed the hand of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was against
        them, to destroy them from the camp, until they had perished.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CSo as soon as all the men of war had perished and were dead
        from among the people, "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u2018Today you are to cross the border of Moab at Ar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And when you approach the territory of the people of Ammon, do not
        harass them or contend with them, for I will not give you any of the land
        of the people of Ammon as a possession, because I have given it to the sons
        of Lot for a possession.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "(It is also counted as a land of Rephaim. Rephaim formerly lived
        there\u2014but the Ammonites call them Zamzummim\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'a people great and many, and tall as the Anakim; but the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        destroyed them before the Ammonites,[[COMMENT(0)]] and they dispossessed
        them and settled in their place, '
      comments:
      - number: '2:21 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'as he did for the people of Esau, who live in Seir, when he destroyed
        the Horites before them and they dispossessed them and settled in their place
        even to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'As for the Avvim, who lived in villages as far as Gaza, the Caphtorim,
        who came from Caphtor, destroyed them and settled in their place.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u2018Rise up, set out on your journey and go over the Valley of
        the Arnon. Behold, I have given into your hand Sihon the Amorite, king of
        Heshbon, and his land. Begin to take possession, and contend with him in
        battle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: The Defeat of King Sihon'
      title: The Defeat of King Sihon
      number: 25
      content: "This day I will begin to put the dread and fear of you on the peoples
        who are under the whole heaven, who shall hear the report of you and shall
        tremble and be in anguish because of you.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CSo I sent messengers from the wilderness of Kedemoth to Sihon
        the king of Heshbon, with words of peace, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u2018Let me pass through your land. I will go only by the road;
        I will turn aside neither to the right nor to the left. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'You shall sell me food for money, that I may eat, and give me water
        for money, that I may drink. Only let me pass through on foot, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "as the sons of Esau who live in Seir and the Moabites who live in
        Ar did for me, until I go over the Jordan into the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God is giving to us.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'But Sihon the king of Heshbon would not let us pass by him, for the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God hardened his spirit and made his heart
        obstinate, that he might give him into your hand, as he is this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u2018Behold, I have
        begun to give Sihon and his land over to you. Begin to take possession, that
        you may occupy his land.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Then Sihon came out against us, he and all his people, to battle
        at Jahaz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God gave him over to us,
        and we defeated him and his sons and all his people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And we captured all his cities at that time and devoted to destruction[[COMMENT(0)]]
        every city, men, women, and children. We left no survivors. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:34 '
        content: That is, set apart (devoted) as an offering to the Lord (for destruction)
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Only the livestock we took as spoil for ourselves, with the plunder
        of the cities that we captured. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'From Aroer, which is on the edge of the Valley of the Arnon, and
        from the city that is in the valley, as far as Gilead, there was not a city
        too high for us. The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God gave all into our
        hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: Only to the land of the sons of Ammon you did not draw near, that
        is, to all the banks of the river Jabbok and the cities of the hill country,
        whatever the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God had forbidden us.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Defeat of King Og'
      title: The Defeat of King Og
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CThen we turned and went up the way to Bashan. And Og the
        king of Bashan came out against us, he and all his people, to battle at Edrei. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u2018Do not fear
        him, for I have given him and all his people and his land into your hand.
        And you shall do to him as you did to Sihon the king of the Amorites, who
        lived at Heshbon.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God gave into our hand Og
        also, the king of Bashan, and all his people, and we struck him down until
        he had no survivor left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And we took all his cities at that time\u2014there was not a city
        that we did not take from them\u2014sixty cities, the whole region of Argob,
        the kingdom of Og in Bashan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'All these were cities fortified with high walls, gates, and bars,
        besides very many unwalled villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And we devoted them to destruction,[[COMMENT(0)]] as we did to Sihon
        the king of Heshbon, devoting to destruction every city, men, women, and
        children. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:6 '
        content: That is, set apart (devoted) as an offering to the Lord (for destruction);
          twice in this verse
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But all the livestock and the spoil of the cities we took as our
        plunder. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So we took the land at that time out of the hand of the two kings
        of the Amorites who were beyond the Jordan, from the Valley of the Arnon
        to Mount Hermon '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '(the Sidonians call Hermon Sirion, while the Amorites call it Senir), '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'all the cities of the tableland and all Gilead and all Bashan, as
        far as Salecah and Edrei, cities of the kingdom of Og in Bashan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '(For only Og the king of Bashan was left of the remnant of the Rephaim.
        Behold, his bed was a bed of iron. Is it not in Rabbah of the Ammonites?
        Nine cubits[[COMMENT(0)]] was its length, and four cubits its breadth, according
        to the common cubit.)  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:11 '
        content: 'A was about 18 inches or 45 centimetersHebrew '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CWhen we took possession of this land at that time, I gave to
        the Reubenites and the Gadites the territory beginning at Aroer, which is
        on the edge of the Valley of the Arnon, and half the hill country of Gilead
        with its cities. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The rest of Gilead, and all Bashan, the kingdom of Og, that is, all
        the region of Argob, I gave to the half-tribe of Manasseh. (All that portion
        of Bashan is called the land of Rephaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Jair the Manassite took all the region of Argob, that is, Bashan,
        as far as the border of the Geshurites and the Maacathites, and called the
        villages after his own name, Havvoth-jair, as it is to this day.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'To Machir I gave Gilead, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'and to the Reubenites and the Gadites I gave the territory from Gilead
        as far as the Valley of the Arnon, with the middle of the valley as a border,
        as far over as the river Jabbok, the border of the Ammonites; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'the Arabah also, with the Jordan as the border, from Chinnereth as
        far as the Sea of the Arabah, the Salt Sea, under the slopes of Pisgah on
        the east.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CAnd I commanded you at that time, saying, \u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God has given you this land to possess. All your men of valor shall
        cross over armed before your brothers, the people of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Only your wives, your little ones, and your livestock (I know that
        you have much livestock) shall remain in the cities that I have given you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "until the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gives rest to your brothers,
        as to you, and they also occupy the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God gives them beyond the Jordan. Then each of you may return to his
        possession which I have given you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And I commanded Joshua at that time, \u2018Your eyes have seen all
        that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has done to these two kings.
        So will the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> do to all the kingdoms into which
        you are crossing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Moses Forbidden to Enter the Land'
      title: Moses Forbidden to Enter the Land
      number: 22
      content: "You shall not fear them, for it is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God who fights for you.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CAnd I pleaded with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> at that
        time, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u2018O Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>, you have only begun to show
        your servant your greatness and your mighty hand. For what god is there in
        heaven or on earth who can do such works and mighty acts as yours? "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Please let me go over and see the good land beyond the Jordan, that
        good hill country and Lebanon.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was angry with me because of
        you and would not listen to me. And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said
        to me, \u2018Enough from you; do not speak to me of this matter again. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Go up to the top of Pisgah and lift up your eyes westward and northward
        and southward and eastward, and look at it with your eyes, for you shall
        not go over this Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "But charge Joshua, and encourage and strengthen him, for he shall
        go over at the head of this people, and he shall put them in possession of
        the land that you shall see.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: So we remained in the valley opposite Beth-peor.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Moses Commands Obedience'
      title: Moses Commands Obedience
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CAnd now, O Israel, listen to the statutes and the rules[[COMMENT(0)]]
        that I am teaching you, and do them, that you may live, and go in and take
        possession of the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of your
        fathers, is giving you. "
      comments:
      - number: '4:1 '
        content: Or ; also verses 5, 8, 14, 45
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'You shall not add to the word that I command you, nor take from it,
        that you may keep the commandments of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God that I command you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Your eyes have seen what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> did at Baal-peor,
        for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God destroyed from among you all
        the men who followed the Baal of Peor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But you who held fast to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God
        are all alive today. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'See, I have taught you statutes and rules, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        my God commanded me, that you should do them in the land that you are entering
        to take possession of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Keep them and do them, for that will be your wisdom and your understanding
        in the sight of the peoples, who, when they hear all these statutes, will
        say, \u2018Surely this great nation is a wise and understanding people.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For what great nation is there that has a god so near to it as the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God is to us, whenever we call upon him? '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And what great nation is there, that has statutes and rules so righteous
        as all this law that I set before you today?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "  \u201COnly take care, and keep your soul diligently, lest you forget
        the things that your eyes have seen, and lest they depart from your heart
        all the days of your life. Make them known to your children and your children\u2019s
        children\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "how on the day that you stood before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God at Horeb, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u2018Gather
        the people to me, that I may let them hear my words, so that they may learn
        to fear me all the days that they live on the earth, and that they may teach
        their children so.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And you came near and stood at the foot of the mountain, while the
        mountain burned with fire to the heart of heaven, wrapped in darkness, cloud,
        and gloom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke to you out of the midst
        of the fire. You heard the sound of words, but saw no form; there was only
        a voice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And he declared to you his covenant, which he commanded you to perform,
        that is, the Ten Commandments,[[COMMENT(0)]]  and he wrote them on two tablets
        of stone. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:13 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '14: Idolatry Forbidden'
      title: Idolatry Forbidden
      number: 14
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> commanded me at that time to
        teach you statutes and rules, that you might do them in the land that you
        are going over to possess.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "  \u201CTherefore watch yourselves very carefully. Since you saw
        no form on the day that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke to you at Horeb
        out of the midst of the fire, "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'beware lest you act corruptly by making a carved image for yourselves,
        in the form of any figure, the likeness of male or female, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'the likeness of any animal that is on the earth, the likeness of
        any winged bird that flies in the air, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'the likeness of anything that creeps on the ground, the likeness
        of any fish that is in the water under the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And beware lest you raise your eyes to heaven, and when you see the
        sun and the moon and the stars, all the host of heaven, you be drawn away
        and bow down to them and serve them, things that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God has allotted to all the peoples under the whole heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has taken you and brought you
        out of the iron furnace, out of Egypt, to be a people of his own inheritance,
        as you are this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Furthermore, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was angry with me because
        of you, and he swore that I should not cross the Jordan, and that I should
        not enter the good land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is
        giving you for an inheritance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For I must die in this land; I must not go over the Jordan. But you
        shall go over and take possession of that good land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Take care, lest you forget the covenant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, which he made with you, and make a carved image, the form of anything
        that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has forbidden you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is a consuming fire,
        a jealous God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CWhen you father children and children\u2019s children, and
        have grown old in the land, if you act corruptly by making a carved image
        in the form of anything, and by doing what is evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, so as to provoke him to anger, "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'I call heaven and earth to witness against you today, that you will
        soon utterly perish from the land that you are going over the Jordan to possess.
        You will not live long in it, but will be utterly destroyed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  will scatter you among the peoples,
        and you will be left few in number among the nations where the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will drive you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And there you will serve gods of wood and stone, the work of human
        hands, that neither see, nor hear, nor eat, nor smell. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'But from there you will seek the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God and you will find him, if you search after him with all your heart and
        with all your soul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'When you are in tribulation, and all these things come upon you in
        the latter days, you will return to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God and obey his voice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: The  Alone Is God'
      title: The  Alone Is God
      number: 31
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is a merciful God. He
        will not leave you or destroy you or forget the covenant with your fathers
        that he swore to them.<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CFor ask now of the days that are past, which were before you,
        since the day that God created man on the earth, and ask from one end of
        heaven to the other, whether such a great thing as this has ever happened
        or was ever heard of. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Did any people ever hear the voice of a god speaking out of the midst
        of the fire, as you have heard, and still live? '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Or has any god ever attempted to go and take a nation for himself
        from the midst of another nation, by trials, by signs, by wonders, and by
        war, by a mighty hand and an outstretched arm, and by great deeds of terror,
        all of which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God did for you in Egypt
        before your eyes? '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'To you it was shown, that you might know that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is God; there is no other besides him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Out of heaven he let you hear his voice, that he might discipline
        you. And on earth he let you see his great fire, and you heard his words
        out of the midst of the fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'And because he loved your fathers and chose their offspring after
        them[[COMMENT(0)]] and brought you out of Egypt with his own presence, by
        his great power, '
      comments:
      - number: '4:37 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'driving out before you nations greater and mightier than you, to
        bring you in, to give you their land for an inheritance, as it is this day, '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'know therefore today, and lay it to your heart, that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is God in heaven above and on the earth beneath; there is no other. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: Cities of Refuge'
      title: Cities of Refuge
      number: 40
      content: "Therefore you shall keep his statutes and his commandments, which
        I command you today, that it may go well with you and with your children
        after you, and that you may prolong your days in the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God is giving you for all time.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Then Moses set apart three cities in the east beyond the Jordan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'that the manslayer might flee there, anyone who kills his neighbor
        unintentionally, without being at enmity with him in time past; he may flee
        to one of these cities and save his life: '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: Introduction to the Law'
      title: Introduction to the Law
      number: 43
      content: 'Bezer in the wilderness on the tableland for the Reubenites, Ramoth
        in Gilead for the Gadites, and Golan in Bashan for the Manassites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'This is the law that Moses set before the people of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'These are the testimonies, the statutes, and the rules, which Moses
        spoke to the people of Israel when they came out of Egypt, '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'beyond the Jordan in the valley opposite Beth-peor, in the land of
        Sihon the king of the Amorites, who lived at Heshbon, whom Moses and the
        people of Israel defeated when they came out of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'And they took possession of his land and the land of Og, the king
        of Bashan, the two kings of the Amorites, who lived to the east beyond the
        Jordan; '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'from Aroer, which is on the edge of the Valley of the Arnon, as far
        as Mount Sirion[[COMMENT(0)]] (that is, Hermon), '
      comments:
      - number: '4:48 '
        content: 'Syriac; Hebrew '
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: together with all the Arabah on the east side of the Jordan as far
        as the Sea of the Arabah, under the slopes of Pisgah.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Ten Commandments'
      title: The Ten Commandments
      number: 1
      content: "  And Moses summoned all Israel and said to them, \u201CHear, O Israel,
        the statutes and the rules that I speak in your hearing today, and you shall
        learn them and be careful to do them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God made a covenant with us in
        Horeb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Not with our fathers did the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> make this
        covenant, but with us, who are all of us here alive today. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke with you face to face at the
        mountain, out of the midst of the fire, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'while I stood between the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and you at
        that time, to declare to you the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        For you were afraid because of the fire, and you did not go up into the mountain.
        He said:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "  \u201C\u2018I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, who
        brought you out of the land of Egypt, out of the house of slavery.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201C\u2018You shall have no other gods before[[COMMENT(0)]] me.  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:7 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201C\u2018You shall not make for yourself a carved image, or any
        likeness of anything that is in heaven above, or that is on the earth beneath,
        or that is in the water under the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'You shall not bow down to them or serve them; for I the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God am a jealous God, visiting the iniquity of the fathers on the children
        to the third and fourth generation of those who hate me, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'but showing steadfast love to thousands[[COMMENT(0)]] of those who
        love me and keep my commandments.  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:10 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201C\u2018You shall not take the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God in vain, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will not hold him guiltless
        who takes his name in vain.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201C\u2018Observe the Sabbath day, to keep it holy, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God commanded you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Six days you shall labor and do all your work, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'but the seventh day is a Sabbath to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God. On it you shall not do any work, you or your son or your daughter
        or your male servant or your female servant, or your ox or your donkey or
        any of your livestock, or the sojourner who is within your gates, that your
        male servant and your female servant may rest as well as you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'You shall remember that you were a slave[[COMMENT(0)]] in the land
        of Egypt, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God brought you out from
        there with a mighty hand and an outstretched arm. Therefore the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God commanded you to keep the Sabbath day.  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:15 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201C\u2018Honor your father and your mother, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God commanded you, that your days may be long, and that it may go well
        with you in the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is giving
        you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "  \u201C\u2018You shall not murder.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:17 '
        content: The Hebrew word also covers causing human death through carelessness
          or negligence
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "  \u201C\u2018And you shall not commit adultery.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201C\u2018And you shall not steal.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201C\u2018And you shall not bear false witness against your neighbor.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201C\u2018And you shall not covet your neighbor\u2019s wife. And
        you shall not desire your neighbor\u2019s house, his field, or his male servant,
        or his female servant, his ox, or his donkey, or anything that is your neighbor\u2019s.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CThese words the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke to all your
        assembly at the mountain out of the midst of the fire, the cloud, and the
        thick darkness, with a loud voice; and he added no more. And he wrote them
        on two tablets of stone and gave them to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And as soon as you heard the voice out of the midst of the darkness,
        while the mountain was burning with fire, you came near to me, all the heads
        of your tribes, and your elders. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And you said, \u2018Behold, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God
        has shown us his glory and greatness, and we have heard his voice out of
        the midst of the fire. This day we have seen God speak with man, and man
        still live. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Now therefore why should we die? For this great fire will consume
        us. If we hear the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God any more,
        we shall die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For who is there of all flesh, that has heard the voice of the living
        God speaking out of the midst of fire as we have, and has still lived? '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Go near and hear all that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God
        will say, and speak to us all that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God
        will speak to you, and we will hear and do it.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CAnd the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> heard your words, when
        you spoke to me. And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u2018I
        have heard the words of this people, which they have spoken to you. They
        are right in all that they have spoken. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Oh that they had such a heart as this always, to fear me and to keep
        all my commandments, that it might go well with them and with their descendants[[COMMENT(0)]]
        forever! '
      comments:
      - number: '5:29 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Go and say to them, \u201CReturn to your tents.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "But you, stand here by me, and I will tell you the whole commandment
        and the statutes and the rules that you shall teach them, that they may do
        them in the land that I am giving them to possess.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'You shall be careful therefore to do as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God has commanded you. You shall not turn aside to the right hand or
        to the left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: You shall walk in all the way that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God has commanded you, that you may live, and that it may go well with
        you, and that you may live long in the land that you shall possess.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Greatest Commandment'
      title: The Greatest Commandment
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CNow this is the commandment\u2014the statutes and the rules[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014that
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God commanded me to teach you, that
        you may do them in the land to which you are going over, to possess it, "
      comments:
      - number: '6:1 '
        content: Or ; also verse 20
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "that you may fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, you and
        your son and your son\u2019s son, by keeping all his statutes and his commandments,
        which I command you, all the days of your life, and that your days may be
        long. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Hear therefore, O Israel, and be careful to do them, that it may
        go well with you, and that you may multiply greatly, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of your fathers, has promised you, in a land flowing with milk and
        honey.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CHear, O Israel: The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God, the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is one.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:4 '
        content: 'Or <span class="ChapterContent_bdit___RrVH">Lord</span>  <span
          class="ChapterContent_bdit___RrVH">Lord</span>; or <span class="ChapterContent_bdit___RrVH">Lord</span> 
          <span class="ChapterContent_bdit___RrVH">Lord</span>  ; or <span class="ChapterContent_bdit___RrVH">Lord</span> 
          <span class="ChapterContent_bdit___RrVH">Lord</span>  '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You shall love the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God with all
        your heart and with all your soul and with all your might. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And these words that I command you today shall be on your heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'You shall teach them diligently to your children, and shall talk
        of them when you sit in your house, and when you walk by the way, and when
        you lie down, and when you rise. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'You shall bind them as a sign on your hand, and they shall be as
        frontlets between your eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'You shall write them on the doorposts of your house and on your gates.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CAnd when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God brings you
        into the land that he swore to your fathers, to Abraham, to Isaac, and to
        Jacob, to give you\u2014with great and good cities that you did not build, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "and houses full of all good things that you did not fill, and cisterns
        that you did not dig, and vineyards and olive trees that you did not plant\u2014and
        when you eat and are full, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'then take care lest you forget the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, who
        brought you out of the land of Egypt, out of the house of slavery. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'It is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God you shall fear. Him
        you shall serve and by his name you shall swear. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "You shall not go after other gods, the gods of the peoples who are
        around you\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God in your midst is a jealous
        God\u2014lest the anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God be kindled
        against you, and he destroy you from off the face of the earth.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  \u201CYou shall not put the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God
        to the test, as you tested him at Massah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'You shall diligently keep the commandments of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, and his testimonies and his statutes, which he has commanded you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And you shall do what is right and good in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        that it may go well with you, and that you may go in and take possession
        of the good land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> swore to give to your
        fathers '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'by thrusting out all your enemies from before you, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has promised.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "  \u201CWhen your son asks you in time to come, \u2018What is the
        meaning of the testimonies and the statutes and the rules that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God has commanded you?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "then you shall say to your son, \u2018We were Pharaoh\u2019s slaves
        in Egypt. And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> brought us out of Egypt with
        a mighty hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> showed signs and wonders, great
        and grievous, against Egypt and against Pharaoh and all his household, before
        our eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And he brought us out from there, that he might bring us in and give
        us the land that he swore to give to our fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> commanded us to do all these
        statutes, to fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God, for our good always,
        that he might preserve us alive, as we are this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And it will be righteousness for us, if we are careful to do all
        this commandment before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God, as he has
        commanded us.\u2019"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Chosen People'
      title: A Chosen People
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CWhen the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God brings you
        into the land that you are entering to take possession of it, and clears
        away many nations before you, the Hittites, the Girgashites, the Amorites,
        the Canaanites, the Perizzites, the Hivites, and the Jebusites, seven nations
        more numerous and mightier than you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God gives them over
        to you, and you defeat them, then you must devote them to complete destruction.[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        You shall make no covenant with them and show no mercy to them. '
      comments:
      - number: '7:2 '
        content: That is, set apart (devote) as an offering to the Lord (for destruction)
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You shall not intermarry with them, giving your daughters to their
        sons or taking their daughters for your sons, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'for they would turn away your sons from following me, to serve other
        gods. Then the anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> would be kindled
        against you, and he would destroy you quickly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But thus shall you deal with them: you shall break down their altars
        and dash in pieces their pillars and chop down their Asherim and burn their
        carved images with fire.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CFor you are a people holy to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God. The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has chosen you to be a
        people for his treasured possession, out of all the peoples who are on the
        face of the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'It was not because you were more in number than any other people
        that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> set his love on you and chose you, for
        you were the fewest of all peoples, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'but it is because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> loves you and is
        keeping the oath that he swore to your fathers, that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has brought you out with a mighty hand and redeemed you from the house of
        slavery, from the hand of Pharaoh king of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Know therefore that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is God,
        the faithful God who keeps covenant and steadfast love with those who love
        him and keep his commandments, to a thousand generations, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and repays to their face those who hate him, by destroying them.
        He will not be slack with one who hates him. He will repay him to his face. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'You shall therefore be careful to do the commandment and the statutes
        and the rules that I command you today.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "  \u201CAnd because you listen to these rules and keep and do them,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will keep with you the covenant
        and the steadfast love that he swore to your fathers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He will love you, bless you, and multiply you. He will also bless
        the fruit of your womb and the fruit of your ground, your grain and your
        wine and your oil, the increase of your herds and the young of your flock,
        in the land that he swore to your fathers to give you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'You shall be blessed above all peoples. There shall not be male or
        female barren among you or among your livestock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will take away from you all sickness,
        and none of the evil diseases of Egypt, which you knew, will he inflict on
        you, but he will lay them on all who hate you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And you shall consume all the peoples that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God will give over to you. Your eye shall not pity them, neither shall
        you serve their gods, for that would be a snare to you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CIf you say in your heart, \u2018These nations are greater than
        I. How can I dispossess them?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'you shall not be afraid of them but you shall remember what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God did to Pharaoh and to all Egypt, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'the great trials that your eyes saw, the signs, the wonders, the
        mighty hand, and the outstretched arm, by which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God brought you out. So will the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God
        do to all the peoples of whom you are afraid. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Moreover, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will send hornets
        among them, until those who are left and hide themselves from you are destroyed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'You shall not be in dread of them, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God is in your midst, a great and awesome God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will clear away these nations
        before you little by little. You may not make an end of them at once,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        lest the wild beasts grow too numerous for you. '
      comments:
      - number: '7:22 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will give them over
        to you and throw them into great confusion, until they are destroyed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And he will give their kings into your hand, and you shall make their
        name perish from under heaven. No one shall be able to stand against you
        until you have destroyed them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The carved images of their gods you shall burn with fire. You shall
        not covet the silver or the gold that is on them or take it for yourselves,
        lest you be ensnared by it, for it is an abomination to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: And you shall not bring an abominable thing into your house and become
        devoted to destruction[[COMMENT(0)]] like it. You shall utterly detest and
        abhor it, for it is devoted to destruction.
      comments:
      - number: '7:26 '
        content: That is, set apart (devoted) as an offering to the Lord (for destruction);
          twice in this verse
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Remember the  Your God'
      title: Remember the  Your God
      number: 1
      content: "<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  \u201CThe whole commandment that I command
        you today you shall be careful to do, that you may live and multiply, and
        go in and possess the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> swore to
        give to your fathers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And you shall remember the whole way that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God has led you these forty years in the wilderness, that he might humble
        you, testing you to know what was in your heart, whether you would keep his
        commandments or not. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And he humbled you and let you hunger and fed you with manna, which
        you did not know, nor did your fathers know, that he might make you know
        that man does not live by bread alone, but man lives by every word[[COMMENT(0)]]
        that comes from the mouth of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:3 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Your clothing did not wear out on you and your foot did not swell
        these forty years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Know then in your heart that, as a man disciplines his son, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God disciplines you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So you shall keep the commandments of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God by walking in his ways and by fearing him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is bringing you into
        a good land, a land of brooks of water, of fountains and springs, flowing
        out in the valleys and hills, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'a land of wheat and barley, of vines and fig trees and pomegranates,
        a land of olive trees and honey, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'a land in which you will eat bread without scarcity, in which you
        will lack nothing, a land whose stones are iron, and out of whose hills you
        can dig copper. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And you shall eat and be full, and you shall bless the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God for the good land he has given you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CTake care lest you forget the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God by not keeping his commandments and his rules and his statutes, which
        I command you today, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'lest, when you have eaten and are full and have built good houses
        and live in them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and when your herds and flocks multiply and your silver and gold
        is multiplied and all that you have is multiplied, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'then your heart be lifted up, and you forget the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt, out of the house of slavery, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'who led you through the great and terrifying wilderness, with its
        fiery serpents and scorpions and thirsty ground where there was no water,
        who brought you water out of the flinty rock, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'who fed you in the wilderness with manna that your fathers did not
        know, that he might humble you and test you, to do you good in the end. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Beware lest you say in your heart, \u2018My power and the might of
        my hand have gotten me this wealth.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'You shall remember the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, for
        it is he who gives you power to get wealth, that he may confirm his covenant
        that he swore to your fathers, as it is this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And if you forget the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God and go
        after other gods and serve them and worship them, I solemnly warn you today
        that you shall surely perish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Like the nations that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> makes to perish
        before you, so shall you perish, because you would not obey the voice of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Not Because of Righteousness'
      title: Not Because of Righteousness
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CHear, O Israel: you are to cross over the Jordan today, to
        go in to dispossess nations greater and mightier than you, cities great and
        fortified up to heaven, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "a people great and tall, the sons of the Anakim, whom you know, and
        of whom you have heard it said, \u2018Who can stand before the sons of Anak?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Know therefore today that he who goes over before you as a consuming
        fire is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God. He will destroy them and
        subdue them before you. So you shall drive them out and make them perish
        quickly, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has promised you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "  \u201CDo not say in your heart, after the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God has thrust them out before you, \u2018It is because of my righteousness
        that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has brought me in to possess this land,\u2019
        whereas it is because of the wickedness of these nations that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is driving them out before you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Not because of your righteousness or the uprightness of your heart
        are you going in to possess their land, but because of the wickedness of
        these nations the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is driving them out
        from before you, and that he may confirm the word that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        swore to your fathers, to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CKnow, therefore, that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God is not giving you this good land to possess because of your righteousness,
        for you are a stubborn people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Remember and do not forget how you provoked the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God to wrath in the wilderness. From the day you came out of the land
        of Egypt until you came to this place, you have been rebellious against the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Even at Horeb you provoked the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> to wrath,
        and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was so angry with you that he was ready
        to destroy you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'When I went up the mountain to receive the tablets of stone, the
        tablets of the covenant that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> made with you,
        I remained on the mountain forty days and forty nights. I neither ate bread
        nor drank water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave me the two tablets of stone
        written with the finger of God, and on them were all the words that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had spoken with you on the mountain out of the midst of the fire on the day
        of the assembly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And at the end of forty days and forty nights the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        gave me the two tablets of stone, the tablets of the covenant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: The Golden Calf'
      title: The Golden Calf
      number: 12
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u2018Arise, go
        down quickly from here, for your people whom you have brought from Egypt
        have acted corruptly. They have turned aside quickly out of the way that
        I commanded them; they have made themselves a metal image.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "  \u201CFurthermore, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me,
        \u2018I have seen this people, and behold, it is a stubborn people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Let me alone, that I may destroy them and blot out their name from
        under heaven. And I will make of you a nation mightier and greater than they.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So I turned and came down from the mountain, and the mountain was
        burning with fire. And the two tablets of the covenant were in my two hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And I looked, and behold, you had sinned against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God. You had made yourselves a golden[[COMMENT(0)]] calf. You had turned
        aside quickly from the way that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had commanded
        you. '
      comments:
      - number: '9:16 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So I took hold of the two tablets and threw them out of my two hands
        and broke them before your eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then I lay prostrate before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  as before,
        forty days and forty nights. I neither ate bread nor drank water, because
        of all the sin that you had committed, in doing what was evil in the sight
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> to provoke him to anger. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For I was afraid of the anger and hot displeasure that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        bore against you, so that he was ready to destroy you. But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        listened to me that time also. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was so angry with Aaron that
        he was ready to destroy him. And I prayed for Aaron also at the same time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then I took the sinful thing, the calf that you had made, and burned
        it with fire and crushed it, grinding it very small, until it was as fine
        as dust. And I threw the dust of it into the brook that ran down from the
        mountain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CAt Taberah also, and at Massah and at Kibroth-hattaavah you
        provoked the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> to wrath. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sent you from Kadesh-barnea,
        saying, \u2018Go up and take possession of the land that I have given you,\u2019
        then you rebelled against the commandment of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God and did not believe him or obey his voice. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'You have been rebellious against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        from the day that I knew you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "  \u201CSo I lay prostrate before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        for these forty days and forty nights, because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had said he would destroy you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And I prayed to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u2018O Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>,
        do not destroy your people and your heritage, whom you have redeemed through
        your greatness, whom you have brought out of Egypt with a mighty hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Remember your servants, Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob. Do not regard
        the stubbornness of this people, or their wickedness or their sin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "lest the land from which you brought us say, \u201CBecause the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        was not able to bring them into the land that he promised them, and because
        he hated them, he has brought them out to put them to death in the wilderness.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "For they are your people and your heritage, whom you brought out
        by your great power and by your outstretched arm.\u2019"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: New Tablets of Stone'
      title: New Tablets of Stone
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CAt that time the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me,
        \u2018Cut for yourself two tablets of stone like the first, and come up to
        me on the mountain and make an ark of wood. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And I will write on the tablets the words that were on the first
        tablets that you broke, and you shall put them in the ark.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So I made an ark of acacia wood, and cut two tablets of stone like
        the first, and went up the mountain with the two tablets in my hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And he wrote on the tablets, in the same writing as before, the Ten
        Commandments[[COMMENT(0)]]  that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had spoken
        to you on the mountain out of the midst of the fire on the day of the assembly.
        And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave them to me. '
      comments:
      - number: '10:4 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then I turned and came down from the mountain and put the tablets
        in the ark that I had made. And there they are, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        commanded me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '(The people of Israel journeyed from Beeroth Bene-jaakan[[COMMENT(0)]]
        to Moserah. There Aaron died, and there he was buried. And his son Eleazar
        ministered as priest in his place. '
      comments:
      - number: '10:6 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'From there they journeyed to Gudgodah, and from Gudgodah to Jotbathah,
        a land with brooks of water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'At that time the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> set apart the tribe
        of Levi to carry the ark of the covenant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        to stand before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> to minister to him and to
        bless in his name, to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Therefore Levi has no portion or inheritance with his brothers. The
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is his inheritance, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God said to him.)  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "  \u201CI myself stayed on the mountain, as at the first time, forty
        days and forty nights, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> listened to me
        that time also. The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was unwilling to destroy
        you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Circumcise Your Heart'
      title: Circumcise Your Heart
      number: 11
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u2018Arise, go on
        your journey at the head of the people, so that they may go in and possess
        the land, which I swore to their fathers to give them.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CAnd now, Israel, what does the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God require of you, but to fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God, to walk in all his ways, to love him, to serve the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God with all your heart and with all your soul, "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and to keep the commandments and statutes of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        which I am commanding you today for your good? '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Behold, to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God belong heaven
        and the heaven of heavens, the earth with all that is in it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Yet the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> set his heart in love on your
        fathers and chose their offspring after them, you above all peoples, as you
        are this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Circumcise therefore the foreskin of your heart, and be no longer
        stubborn. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is God of gods and Lord
        of lords, the great, the mighty, and the awesome God, who is not partial
        and takes no bribe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He executes justice for the fatherless and the widow, and loves the
        sojourner, giving him food and clothing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Love the sojourner, therefore, for you were sojourners in the land
        of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'You shall fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God. You shall
        serve him and hold fast to him, and by his name you shall swear. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He is your praise. He is your God, who has done for you these great
        and terrifying things that your eyes have seen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Your fathers went down to Egypt seventy persons, and now the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God has made you as numerous as the stars of heaven.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Love and Serve the '
      title: 'Love and Serve the '
      number: 1
      content: "<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>    \u201CYou shall therefore love the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God and keep his charge, his statutes, his
        rules, and his commandments always. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And consider today (since I am not speaking to your children who
        have not known or seen it), consider the discipline[[COMMENT(0)]] of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, his greatness, his mighty hand and
        his outstretched arm, '
      comments:
      - number: '11:2 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'his signs and his deeds that he did in Egypt to Pharaoh the king
        of Egypt and to all his land, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and what he did to the army of Egypt, to their horses and to their
        chariots, how he made the water of the Red Sea flow over them as they pursued
        after you, and how the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has destroyed them to
        this day, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and what he did to you in the wilderness, until you came to this
        place, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and what he did to Dathan and Abiram the sons of Eliab, son of Reuben,
        how the earth opened its mouth and swallowed them up, with their households,
        their tents, and every living thing that followed them, in the midst of all
        Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For your eyes have seen all the great work of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        that he did.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CYou shall therefore keep the whole commandment that I command
        you today, that you may be strong, and go in and take possession of the land
        that you are going over to possess, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'and that you may live long in the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        swore to your fathers to give to them and to their offspring, a land flowing
        with milk and honey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For the land that you are entering to take possession of it is not
        like the land of Egypt, from which you have come, where you sowed your seed
        and irrigated it,[[COMMENT(0)]] like a garden of vegetables. '
      comments:
      - number: '11:10 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But the land that you are going over to possess is a land of hills
        and valleys, which drinks water by the rain from heaven, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'a land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God cares for. The
        eyes of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God are always upon it, from
        the beginning of the year to the end of the year.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CAnd if you will indeed obey my commandments that I command
        you today, to love the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, and to serve
        him with all your heart and with all your soul, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'he[[COMMENT(0)]] will give the rain for your land in its season,
        the early rain and the later rain, that you may gather in your grain and
        your wine and your oil. '
      comments:
      - number: '11:14 '
        content: Samaritan, Septuagint, Vulgate; Hebrew ; also verse 15
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And he will give grass in your fields for your livestock, and you
        shall eat and be full. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Take care lest your heart be deceived, and you turn aside and serve
        other gods and worship them; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'then the anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will be kindled
        against you, and he will shut up the heavens, so that there will be no rain,
        and the land will yield no fruit, and you will perish quickly off the good
        land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is giving you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "  \u201CYou shall therefore lay up these words of mine in your heart
        and in your soul, and you shall bind them as a sign on your hand, and they
        shall be as frontlets between your eyes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'You shall teach them to your children, talking of them when you are
        sitting in your house, and when you are walking by the way, and when you
        lie down, and when you rise. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'You shall write them on the doorposts of your house and on your gates, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'that your days and the days of your children may be multiplied in
        the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> swore to your fathers to give
        them, as long as the heavens are above the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For if you will be careful to do all this commandment that I command
        you to do, loving the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, walking in all
        his ways, and holding fast to him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  will drive out all these nations
        before you, and you will dispossess nations greater and mightier than you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Every place on which the sole of your foot treads shall be yours.
        Your territory shall be from the wilderness to[[COMMENT(0)]] the Lebanon
        and from the River, the river Euphrates, to the western sea. '
      comments:
      - number: '11:24 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'No one shall be able to stand against you. The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God will lay the fear of you and the dread of you on all the land that
        you shall tread, as he promised you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "  \u201CSee, I am setting before you today a blessing and a curse: "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'the blessing, if you obey the commandments of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, which I command you today, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'and the curse, if you do not obey the commandments of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, but turn aside from the way that I am commanding you today, to
        go after other gods that you have not known. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God brings you into
        the land that you are entering to take possession of it, you shall set the
        blessing on Mount Gerizim and the curse on Mount Ebal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Are they not beyond the Jordan, west of the road, toward the going
        down of the sun, in the land of the Canaanites who live in the Arabah, opposite
        Gilgal, beside the oak[[COMMENT(0)]] of Moreh? '
      comments:
      - number: '11:30 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Syriac; see Genesis 12:6. Hebrew , or '
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'For you are to cross over the Jordan to go in to take possession
        of the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is giving you.
        And when you possess it and live in it, '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: you shall be careful to do all the statutes and the rules that I am
        setting before you today.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The \u2019s Chosen Place of Worship"
      title: "The \u2019s Chosen Place of Worship"
      number: 1
      content: "<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>    \u201CThese are the statutes and rules
        that you shall be careful to do in the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of your fathers, has given you to possess, all the days that you
        live on the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'You shall surely destroy all the places where the nations whom you
        shall dispossess served their gods, on the high mountains and on the hills
        and under every green tree. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You shall tear down their altars and dash in pieces their pillars
        and burn their Asherim with fire. You shall chop down the carved images of
        their gods and destroy their name out of that place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'You shall not worship the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God in
        that way. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But you shall seek the place that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God will choose out of all your tribes to put his name and make his
        habitation[[COMMENT(0)]] there. There you shall go, '
      comments:
      - number: '12:5 '
        content: 'Or   '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and there you shall bring your burnt offerings and your sacrifices,
        your tithes and the contribution that you present, your vow offerings, your
        freewill offerings, and the firstborn of your herd and of your flock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And there you shall eat before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God, and you shall rejoice, you and your households, in all that you undertake,
        in which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has blessed you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CYou shall not do according to all that we are doing here today,
        everyone doing whatever is right in his own eyes, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'for you have not as yet come to the rest and to the inheritance that
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is giving you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But when you go over the Jordan and live in the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God is giving you to inherit, and when he gives you rest from all your
        enemies around, so that you live in safety, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'then to the place that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will
        choose, to make his name dwell there, there you shall bring all that I command
        you: your burnt offerings and your sacrifices, your tithes and the contribution
        that you present, and all your finest vow offerings that you vow to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And you shall rejoice before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God, you and your sons and your daughters, your male servants and your female
        servants, and the Levite that is within your towns, since he has no portion
        or inheritance with you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Take care that you do not offer your burnt offerings at any place
        that you see, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'but at the place that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will choose
        in one of your tribes, there you shall offer your burnt offerings, and there
        you shall do all that I am commanding you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CHowever, you may slaughter and eat meat within any of your
        towns, as much as you desire, according to the blessing of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God that he has given you. The unclean and the clean may eat of it,
        as of the gazelle and as of the deer. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Only you shall not eat the blood; you shall pour it out on the earth
        like water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'You may not eat within your towns the tithe of your grain or of your
        wine or of your oil, or the firstborn of your herd or of your flock, or any
        of your vow offerings that you vow, or your freewill offerings or the contribution
        that you present, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'but you shall eat them before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God in the place that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will choose,
        you and your son and your daughter, your male servant and your female servant,
        and the Levite who is within your towns. And you shall rejoice before the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God in all that you undertake. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Take care that you do not neglect the Levite as long as you live
        in your land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CWhen the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God enlarges your
        territory, as he has promised you, and you say, \u2018I will eat meat,\u2019
        because you crave meat, you may eat meat whenever you desire. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'If the place that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will choose
        to put his name there is too far from you, then you may kill any of your
        herd or your flock, which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has given you,
        as I have commanded you, and you may eat within your towns whenever you desire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Just as the gazelle or the deer is eaten, so you may eat of it. The
        unclean and the clean alike may eat of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Only be sure that you do not eat the blood, for the blood is the
        life, and you shall not eat the life with the flesh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'You shall not eat it; you shall pour it out on the earth like water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'You shall not eat it, that all may go well with you and with your
        children after you, when you do what is right in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'But the holy things that are due from you, and your vow offerings,
        you shall take, and you shall go to the place that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will choose, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'and offer your burnt offerings, the flesh and the blood, on the altar
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God. The blood of your sacrifices
        shall be poured out on the altar of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God, but the flesh you may eat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: Warning Against Idolatry'
      title: Warning Against Idolatry
      number: 28
      content: 'Be careful to obey all these words that I command you, that it may
        go well with you and with your children after you forever, when you do what
        is good and right in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CWhen the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God cuts off before
        you the nations whom you go in to dispossess, and you dispossess them and
        dwell in their land, "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "take care that you be not ensnared to follow them, after they have
        been destroyed before you, and that you do not inquire about their gods,
        saying, \u2018How did these nations serve their gods?\u2014that I also may
        do the same.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'You shall not worship the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God in
        that way, for every abominable thing that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        hates they have done for their gods, for they even burn their sons and their
        daughters in the fire to their gods.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "  [[COMMENT(0)]] \u201CEverything that I command you, you shall be
        careful to do. You shall not add to it or take from it."
      comments:
      - number: '12:32 '
        content: '  Ch 13:1 in Hebrew  '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CIf a prophet or a dreamer of dreams arises among you and
        gives you a sign or a wonder, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "and the sign or wonder that he tells you comes to pass, and if he
        says, \u2018Let us go after other gods,\u2019 which you have not known, \u2018and
        let us serve them,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'you shall not listen to the words of that prophet or that dreamer
        of dreams. For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is testing you, to
        know whether you love the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God with all your
        heart and with all your soul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'You shall walk after the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God and
        fear him and keep his commandments and obey his voice, and you shall serve
        him and hold fast to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But that prophet or that dreamer of dreams shall be put to death,
        because he has taught rebellion against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt and redeemed you out of the
        house of slavery, to make you leave the way in which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God commanded you to walk. So you shall purge the evil[[COMMENT(0)]]
        from your midst.  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:5 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "  \u201CIf your brother, the son of your mother, or your son or your
        daughter or the wife you embrace[[COMMENT(0)]] or your friend who is as your
        own soul entices you secretly, saying, \u2018Let us go and serve other gods,\u2019
        which neither you nor your fathers have known, "
      comments:
      - number: '13:6 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'some of the gods of the peoples who are around you, whether near
        you or far off from you, from the one end of the earth to the other, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'you shall not yield to him or listen to him, nor shall your eye pity
        him, nor shall you spare him, nor shall you conceal him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But you shall kill him. Your hand shall be first against him to put
        him to death, and afterward the hand of all the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'You shall stone him to death with stones, because he sought to draw
        you away from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, who brought you out
        of the land of Egypt, out of the house of slavery. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And all Israel shall hear and fear and never again do any such wickedness
        as this among you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CIf you hear in one of your cities, which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God is giving you to dwell there, "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "that certain worthless fellows have gone out among you and have drawn
        away the inhabitants of their city, saying, \u2018Let us go and serve other
        gods,\u2019 which you have not known, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'then you shall inquire and make search and ask diligently. And behold,
        if it be true and certain that such an abomination has been done among you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'you shall surely put the inhabitants of that city to the sword, devoting
        it to destruction,[[COMMENT(0)]] all who are in it and its cattle, with the
        edge of the sword. '
      comments:
      - number: '13:15 '
        content: That is, setting apart (devoting) as an offering to the Lord (for
          destruction)
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'You shall gather all its spoil into the midst of its open square
        and burn the city and all its spoil with fire, as a whole burnt offering
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God. It shall be a heap forever.
        It shall not be built again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'None of the devoted things shall stick to your hand, that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        may turn from the fierceness of his anger and show you mercy and have compassion
        on you and multiply you, as he swore to your fathers, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: if you obey the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God,
        keeping all his commandments that I am commanding you today, and doing what
        is right in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Clean and Unclean Food'
      title: Clean and Unclean Food
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CYou are the sons of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God. You shall not cut yourselves or make any baldness on your foreheads
        for the dead. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For you are a people holy to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has chosen you to be a people for
        his treasured possession, out of all the peoples who are on the face of the
        earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "  \u201CYou shall not eat any abomination. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'These are the animals you may eat: the ox, the sheep, the goat, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'the deer, the gazelle, the roebuck, the wild goat, the ibex,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the antelope, and the mountain sheep. '
      comments:
      - number: '14:5 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Every animal that parts the hoof and has the hoof cloven in two and
        chews the cud, among the animals, you may eat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Yet of those that chew the cud or have the hoof cloven you shall
        not eat these: the camel, the hare, and the rock badger, because they chew
        the cud but do not part the hoof, are unclean for you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the pig, because it parts the hoof but does not chew the cud,
        is unclean for you. Their flesh you shall not eat, and their carcasses you
        shall not touch.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201COf all that are in the waters you may eat these: whatever has
        fins and scales you may eat. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And whatever does not have fins and scales you shall not eat; it
        is unclean for you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CYou may eat all clean birds. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But these are the ones that you shall not eat: the eagle,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the bearded vulture, the black vulture, '
      comments:
      - number: '14:12 '
        content: The identity of many of these birds is uncertain
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'the kite, the falcon of any kind; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'every raven of any kind; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'the ostrich, the nighthawk, the sea gull, the hawk of any kind; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'the little owl and the short-eared owl, the barn owl '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'and the tawny owl, the carrion vulture and the cormorant, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'the stork, the heron of any kind; the hoopoe and the bat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And all winged insects are unclean for you; they shall not be eaten. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'All clean winged things you may eat.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Tithes'
      title: Tithes
      number: 21
      content: "  \u201CYou shall not eat anything that has died naturally. You may
        give it to the sojourner who is within your towns, that he may eat it, or
        you may sell it to a foreigner. For you are a people holy to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God.  \u201CYou shall not boil a young goat in its mother\u2019s milk.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "  \u201CYou shall tithe all the yield of your seed that comes from
        the field year by year. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, in the place
        that he will choose, to make his name dwell there, you shall eat the tithe
        of your grain, of your wine, and of your oil, and the firstborn of your herd
        and flock, that you may learn to fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God always. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And if the way is too long for you, so that you are not able to carry
        the tithe, when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God blesses you, because
        the place is too far from you, which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God chooses, to set his name there, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'then you shall turn it into money and bind up the money in your hand
        and go to the place that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God chooses '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "and spend the money for whatever you desire\u2014oxen or sheep or
        wine or strong drink, whatever your appetite craves. And you shall eat there
        before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God and rejoice, you and your
        household. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And you shall not neglect the Levite who is within your towns, for
        he has no portion or inheritance with you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "  \u201CAt the end of every three years you shall bring out all the
        tithe of your produce in the same year and lay it up within your towns. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: And the Levite, because he has no portion or inheritance with you,
        and the sojourner, the fatherless, and the widow, who are within your towns,
        shall come and eat and be filled, that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God may bless you in all the work of your hands that you do.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Sabbatical Year'
      title: The Sabbatical Year
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CAt the end of every seven years you shall grant a release. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And this is the manner of the release: every creditor shall release
        what he has lent to his neighbor. He shall not exact it of his neighbor,
        his brother, because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s release has been
        proclaimed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Of a foreigner you may exact it, but whatever of yours is with your
        brother your hand shall release. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But there will be no poor among you; for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will bless you in the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God
        is giving you for an inheritance to possess\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'if only you will strictly obey the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, being careful to do all this commandment that I command you today. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will bless you, as he
        promised you, and you shall lend to many nations, but you shall not borrow,
        and you shall rule over many nations, but they shall not rule over you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CIf among you, one of your brothers should become poor, in any
        of your towns within your land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God is giving you, you shall not harden your heart or shut your hand against
        your poor brother, "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'but you shall open your hand to him and lend him sufficient for his
        need, whatever it may be. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Take care lest there be an unworthy thought in your heart and you
        say, \u2018The seventh year, the year of release is near,\u2019 and your
        eye look grudgingly[[COMMENT(0)]] on your poor brother, and you give him
        nothing, and he cry to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> against you, and you
        be guilty of sin. "
      comments:
      - number: '15:9 '
        content: Or ; also verse 10
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'You shall give to him freely, and your heart shall not be grudging
        when you give to him, because for this the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God will bless you in all your work and in all that you undertake. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For there will never cease to be poor in the land. Therefore I command
        you, \u2018You shall open wide your hand to your brother, to the needy and
        to the poor, in your land.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "  \u201CIf your brother, a Hebrew man or a Hebrew woman, is sold[[COMMENT(0)]]
        to you, he shall serve you six years, and in the seventh year you shall let
        him go free from you. "
      comments:
      - number: '15:12 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And when you let him go free from you, you shall not let him go empty-handed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'You shall furnish him liberally out of your flock, out of your threshing
        floor, and out of your winepress. As the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God has blessed you, you shall give to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'You shall remember that you were a slave in the land of Egypt, and
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God redeemed you; therefore I command
        you this today. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But if he says to you, \u2018I will not go out from you,\u2019 because
        he loves you and your household, since he is well-off with you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'then you shall take an awl, and put it through his ear into the door,
        and he shall be your slave[[COMMENT(0)]] forever. And to your female slave
        you shall do the same. '
      comments:
      - number: '15:17 '
        content: 'Or ; the Hebrew term designates a range of social and economic
          roles (see Preface)Or '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'It shall not seem hard to you when you let him go free from you,
        for at half the cost of a hired worker he has served you six years. So the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will bless you in all that you do.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "  \u201CAll the firstborn males that are born of your herd and flock
        you shall dedicate to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God. You shall
        do no work with the firstborn of your herd, nor shear the firstborn of your
        flock. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'You shall eat it, you and your household, before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God year by year at the place that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will
        choose. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But if it has any blemish, if it is lame or blind or has any serious
        blemish whatever, you shall not sacrifice it to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'You shall eat it within your towns. The unclean and the clean alike
        may eat it, as though it were a gazelle or a deer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Only you shall not eat its blood; you shall pour it out on the ground
        like water.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Passover'
      title: Passover
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CObserve the month of Abib and keep the Passover to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, for in the month of Abib the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God
        brought you out of Egypt by night. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And you shall offer the Passover sacrifice to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, from the flock or the herd, at the place that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will choose, to make his name dwell there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "You shall eat no leavened bread with it. Seven days you shall eat
        it with unleavened bread, the bread of affliction\u2014for you came out of
        the land of Egypt in haste\u2014that all the days of your life you may remember
        the day when you came out of the land of Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'No leaven shall be seen with you in all your territory for seven
        days, nor shall any of the flesh that you sacrifice on the evening of the
        first day remain all night until morning. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You may not offer the Passover sacrifice within any of your towns
        that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is giving you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'but at the place that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will
        choose, to make his name dwell in it, there you shall offer the Passover
        sacrifice, in the evening at sunset, at the time you came out of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And you shall cook it and eat it at the place that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God will choose. And in the morning you shall turn and go to your tents. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: The Feast of Weeks'
      title: The Feast of Weeks
      number: 8
      content: 'For six days you shall eat unleavened bread, and on the seventh day
        there shall be a solemn assembly to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God. You shall do no work on it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "  \u201CYou shall count seven weeks. Begin to count the seven weeks
        from the time the sickle is first put to the standing grain. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then you shall keep the Feast of Weeks to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God with the tribute of a freewill offering from your hand, which you
        shall give as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God blesses you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And you shall rejoice before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God, you and your son and your daughter, your male servant and your female
        servant, the Levite who is within your towns, the sojourner, the fatherless,
        and the widow who are among you, at the place that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God will choose, to make his name dwell there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: The Feast of Booths'
      title: The Feast of Booths
      number: 12
      content: 'You shall remember that you were a slave in Egypt; and you shall
        be careful to observe these statutes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "  \u201CYou shall keep the Feast of Booths seven days, when you have
        gathered in the produce from your threshing floor and your winepress. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'You shall rejoice in your feast, you and your son and your daughter,
        your male servant and your female servant, the Levite, the sojourner, the
        fatherless, and the widow who are within your towns. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For seven days you shall keep the feast to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God at the place that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will choose, because
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will bless you in all your produce
        and in all the work of your hands, so that you will be altogether joyful.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  \u201CThree times a year all your males shall appear before the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God at the place that he will choose: at
        the Feast of Unleavened Bread, at the Feast of Weeks, and at the Feast of
        Booths. They shall not appear before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> empty-handed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Justice'
      title: Justice
      number: 17
      content: 'Every man shall give as he is able, according to the blessing of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God that he has given you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CYou shall appoint judges and officers in all your towns that
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is giving you, according to your
        tribes, and they shall judge the people with righteous judgment. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'You shall not pervert justice. You shall not show partiality, and
        you shall not accept a bribe, for a bribe blinds the eyes of the wise and
        subverts the cause of the righteous. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Forbidden Forms of Worship'
      title: Forbidden Forms of Worship
      number: 20
      content: 'Justice, and only justice, you shall follow, that you may live and
        inherit the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is giving
        you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CYou shall not plant any tree as an Asherah beside the altar
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God that you shall make. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: And you shall not set up a pillar, which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God hates.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "    \u201CYou shall not sacrifice to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God an ox or a sheep in which is a blemish, any defect whatever, for
        that is an abomination to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "  \u201CIf there is found among you, within any of your towns that
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is giving you, a man or woman who
        does what is evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God,
        in transgressing his covenant, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and has gone and served other gods and worshiped them, or the sun
        or the moon or any of the host of heaven, which I have forbidden, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and it is told you and you hear of it, then you shall inquire diligently,
        and if it is true and certain that such an abomination has been done in Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'then you shall bring out to your gates that man or woman who has
        done this evil thing, and you shall stone that man or woman to death with
        stones. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'On the evidence of two witnesses or of three witnesses the one who
        is to die shall be put to death; a person shall not be put to death on the
        evidence of one witness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Legal Decisions by Priests and Judges'
      title: Legal Decisions by Priests and Judges
      number: 7
      content: 'The hand of the witnesses shall be first against him to put him to
        death, and afterward the hand of all the people. So you shall purge[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the evil from your midst.  '
      comments:
      - number: '17:7 '
        content: Septuagint ; also verse 12Or ; also verse 12
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CIf any case arises requiring decision between one kind of homicide
        and another, one kind of legal right and another, or one kind of assault
        and another, any case within your towns that is too difficult for you, then
        you shall arise and go up to the place that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God will choose. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And you shall come to the Levitical priests and to the judge who
        is in office in those days, and you shall consult them, and they shall declare
        to you the decision. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then you shall do according to what they declare to you from that
        place that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will choose. And you shall be
        careful to do according to all that they direct you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'According to the instructions that they give you, and according to
        the decision which they pronounce to you, you shall do. You shall not turn
        aside from the verdict that they declare to you, either to the right hand
        or to the left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The man who acts presumptuously by not obeying the priest who stands
        to minister there before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, or the
        judge, that man shall die. So you shall purge the evil from Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: "13: Laws Concerning Israel\u2019s Kings"
      title: "Laws Concerning Israel\u2019s Kings"
      number: 13
      content: 'And all the people shall hear and fear and not act presumptuously
        again.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CWhen you come to the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God is giving you, and you possess it and dwell in it and then say,
        \u2018I will set a king over me, like all the nations that are around me,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'you may indeed set a king over you whom the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God will choose. One from among your brothers you shall set as king
        over you. You may not put a foreigner over you, who is not your brother. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Only he must not acquire many horses for himself or cause the people
        to return to Egypt in order to acquire many horses, since the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has said to you, \u2018You shall never return that way again.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And he shall not acquire many wives for himself, lest his heart turn
        away, nor shall he acquire for himself excessive silver and gold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CAnd when he sits on the throne of his kingdom, he shall write
        for himself in a book a copy of this law, approved by[[COMMENT(0)]] the Levitical
        priests. "
      comments:
      - number: '17:18 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And it shall be with him, and he shall read in it all the days of
        his life, that he may learn to fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> his God
        by keeping all the words of this law and these statutes, and doing them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: that his heart may not be lifted up above his brothers, and that he
        may not turn aside from the commandment, either to the right hand or to the
        left, so that he may continue long in his kingdom, he and his children, in
        Israel.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Provision for Priests and Levites'
      title: Provision for Priests and Levites
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CThe Levitical priests, all the tribe of Levi, shall have
        no portion or inheritance with Israel. They shall eat the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        food offerings[[COMMENT(0)]] as their inheritance. "
      comments:
      - number: '18:1 '
        content: 'Or <span class="ChapterContent_bdit___RrVH">Lord</span>  Hebrew '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'They shall have no inheritance among their brothers; the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is their inheritance, as he promised them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And this shall be the priests\u2019 due from the people, from those
        offering a sacrifice, whether an ox or a sheep: they shall give to the priest
        the shoulder and the two cheeks and the stomach. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The firstfruits of your grain, of your wine and of your oil, and
        the first fleece of your sheep, you shall give him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has chosen him out of
        all your tribes to stand and minister in the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        him and his sons for all time.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CAnd if a Levite comes from any of your towns out of all Israel,
        where he lives\u2014and he may come when he desires[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014to
        the place that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will choose, "
      comments:
      - number: '18:6 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and ministers in the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> his
        God, like all his fellow Levites who stand to minister there before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Abominable Practices'
      title: Abominable Practices
      number: 8
      content: 'then he may have equal portions to eat, besides what he receives
        from the sale of his patrimony.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '18:8 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CWhen you come into the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God is giving you, you shall not learn to follow the abominable practices
        of those nations. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'There shall not be found among you anyone who burns his son or his
        daughter as an offering,[[COMMENT(0)]] anyone who practices divination or
        tells fortunes or interprets omens, or a sorcerer '
      comments:
      - number: '18:10 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'or a charmer or a medium or a necromancer or one who inquires of
        the dead, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'for whoever does these things is an abomination to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        And because of these abominations the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God
        is driving them out before you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'You shall be blameless before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: A New Prophet like Moses'
      title: A New Prophet like Moses
      number: 14
      content: 'for these nations, which you are about to dispossess, listen to fortune-tellers
        and to diviners. But as for you, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God
        has not allowed you to do this.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "  \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will raise up for
        you a prophet like me from among you, from your brothers\u2014it is to him
        you shall listen\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "just as you desired of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God at
        Horeb on the day of the assembly, when you said, \u2018Let me not hear again
        the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> my God or see this great fire
        any more, lest I die.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u2018They are right
        in what they have spoken. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'I will raise up for them a prophet like you from among their brothers.
        And I will put my words in his mouth, and he shall speak to them all that
        I command him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And whoever will not listen to my words that he shall speak in my
        name, I myself will require it of him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But the prophet who presumes to speak a word in my name that I have
        not commanded him to speak, or[[COMMENT(0)]] who speaks in the name of other
        gods, that same prophet shall die.\u2019 "
      comments:
      - number: '18:20 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And if you say in your heart, \u2018How may we know the word that
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has not spoken?\u2019\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: when a prophet speaks in the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        if the word does not come to pass or come true, that is a word that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has not spoken; the prophet has spoken it presumptuously. You need not be
        afraid of him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Laws Concerning Cities of Refuge'
      title: Laws Concerning Cities of Refuge
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CWhen the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God cuts off the
        nations whose land the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is giving you,
        and you dispossess them and dwell in their cities and in their houses, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'you shall set apart three cities for yourselves in the land that
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is giving you to possess. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You shall measure the distances[[COMMENT(0)]] and divide into three
        parts the area of the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God
        gives you as a possession, so that any manslayer can flee to them.  '
      comments:
      - number: '19:3 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CThis is the provision for the manslayer, who by fleeing there
        may save his life. If anyone kills his neighbor unintentionally without having
        hated him in the past\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "as when someone goes into the forest with his neighbor to cut wood,
        and his hand swings the axe to cut down a tree, and the head slips from the
        handle and strikes his neighbor so that he dies\u2014he may flee to one of
        these cities and live, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'lest the avenger of blood in hot anger pursue the manslayer and overtake
        him, because the way is long, and strike him fatally, though the man did
        not deserve to die, since he had not hated his neighbor in the past. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Therefore I command you, You shall set apart three cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And if the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God enlarges your territory,
        as he has sworn to your fathers, and gives you all the land that he promised
        to give to your fathers\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "provided you are careful to keep all this commandment, which I command
        you today, by loving the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God and by walking
        ever in his ways\u2014then you shall add three other cities to these three, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'lest innocent blood be shed in your land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God is giving you for an inheritance, and so the guilt of bloodshed
        be upon you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CBut if anyone hates his neighbor and lies in wait for him and
        attacks him and strikes him fatally so that he dies, and he flees into one
        of these cities, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'then the elders of his city shall send and take him from there, and
        hand him over to the avenger of blood, so that he may die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Property Boundaries'
      title: Property Boundaries
      number: 13
      content: 'Your eye shall not pity him, but you shall purge the guilt of innocent
        blood[[COMMENT(0)]] from Israel, so that it may be well with you.  '
      comments:
      - number: '19:13 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '14: Laws Concerning Witnesses'
      title: Laws Concerning Witnesses
      number: 14
      content: "  \u201CYou shall not move your neighbor\u2019s landmark, which the
        men of old have set, in the inheritance that you will hold in the land that
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is giving you to possess.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CA single witness shall not suffice against a person for any
        crime or for any wrong in connection with any offense that he has committed.
        Only on the evidence of two witnesses or of three witnesses shall a charge
        be established. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'If a malicious witness arises to accuse a person of wrongdoing, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'then both parties to the dispute shall appear before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        before the priests and the judges who are in office in those days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The judges shall inquire diligently, and if the witness is a false
        witness and has accused his brother falsely, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'then you shall do to him as he had meant to do to his brother. So
        you shall purge the evil[[COMMENT(0)]] from your midst. '
      comments:
      - number: '19:19 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And the rest shall hear and fear, and shall never again commit any
        such evil among you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Your eye shall not pity. It shall be life for life, eye for eye, tooth
        for tooth, hand for hand, foot for foot.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Laws Concerning Warfare'
      title: Laws Concerning Warfare
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CWhen you go out to war against your enemies, and see horses
        and chariots and an army larger than your own, you shall not be afraid of
        them, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is with you, who brought
        you up out of the land of Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And when you draw near to the battle, the priest shall come forward
        and speak to the people '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and shall say to them, \u2018Hear, O Israel, today you are drawing
        near for battle against your enemies: let not your heart faint. Do not fear
        or panic or be in dread of them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is he who goes with
        you to fight for you against your enemies, to give you the victory.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then the officers shall speak to the people, saying, \u2018Is there
        any man who has built a new house and has not dedicated it? Let him go back
        to his house, lest he die in the battle and another man dedicate it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And is there any man who has planted a vineyard and has not enjoyed
        its fruit? Let him go back to his house, lest he die in the battle and another
        man enjoy its fruit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And is there any man who has betrothed a wife and has not taken her?
        Let him go back to his house, lest he die in the battle and another man take
        her.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And the officers shall speak further to the people, and say, \u2018Is
        there any man who is fearful and fainthearted? Let him go back to his house,
        lest he make the heart of his fellows melt like his own.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And when the officers have finished speaking to the people, then
        commanders shall be appointed at the head of the people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CWhen you draw near to a city to fight against it, offer terms
        of peace to it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And if it responds to you peaceably and it opens to you, then all
        the people who are found in it shall do forced labor for you and shall serve
        you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But if it makes no peace with you, but makes war against you, then
        you shall besiege it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God gives it into your
        hand, you shall put all its males to the sword, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'but the women and the little ones, the livestock, and everything
        else in the city, all its spoil, you shall take as plunder for yourselves.
        And you shall enjoy the spoil of your enemies, which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God has given you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Thus you shall do to all the cities that are very far from you, which
        are not cities of the nations here. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But in the cities of these peoples that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God is giving you for an inheritance, you shall save alive nothing that
        breathes, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'but you shall devote them to complete destruction,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the Hittites and the Amorites, the Canaanites and the Perizzites, the Hivites
        and the Jebusites, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has commanded, '
      comments:
      - number: '20:17 '
        content: That is, set apart (devote) as an offering to the Lord (for destruction)
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'that they may not teach you to do according to all their abominable
        practices that they have done for their gods, and so you sin against the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CWhen you besiege a city for a long time, making war against
        it in order to take it, you shall not destroy its trees by wielding an axe
        against them. You may eat from them, but you shall not cut them down. Are
        the trees in the field human, that they should be besieged by you? "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Only the trees that you know are not trees for food you may destroy
        and cut down, that you may build siegeworks against the city that makes war
        with you, until it falls.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Atonement for Unsolved Murders'
      title: Atonement for Unsolved Murders
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CIf in the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God is giving you to possess someone is found slain, lying in the open country,
        and it is not known who killed him, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'then your elders and your judges shall come out, and they shall measure
        the distance to the surrounding cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And the elders of the city that is nearest to the slain man shall
        take a heifer that has never been worked and that has not pulled in a yoke. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And the elders of that city shall bring the heifer down to a valley
        with running water, which is neither plowed nor sown, and shall break the
        heifer\u2019s neck there in the valley. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then the priests, the sons of Levi, shall come forward, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God has chosen them to minister to him and to bless in the name of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and by their word every dispute and every assault
        shall be settled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And all the elders of that city nearest to the slain man shall wash
        their hands over the heifer whose neck was broken in the valley, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "and they shall testify, \u2018Our hands did not shed this blood,
        nor did our eyes see it shed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Accept atonement, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, for your people
        Israel, whom you have redeemed, and do not set the guilt of innocent blood
        in the midst of your people Israel, so that their blood guilt be atoned for.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Marrying Female Captives'
      title: Marrying Female Captives
      number: 9
      content: 'So you shall purge the guilt of innocent blood from your midst, when
        you do what is right in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CWhen you go out to war against your enemies, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God gives them into your hand and you take them captive, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'and you see among the captives a beautiful woman, and you desire
        to take her to be your wife, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and you bring her home to your house, she shall shave her head and
        pare her nails. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And she shall take off the clothes in which she was captured and
        shall remain in your house and lament her father and her mother a full month.
        After that you may go in to her and be her husband, and she shall be your
        wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Inheritance Rights of the Firstborn'
      title: Inheritance Rights of the Firstborn
      number: 14
      content: 'But if you no longer delight in her, you shall let her go where she
        wants. But you shall not sell her for money, nor shall you treat her as a
        slave, since you have humiliated her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CIf a man has two wives, the one loved and the other unloved,
        and both the loved and the unloved have borne him children, and if the firstborn
        son belongs to the unloved,[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '21:15 '
        content: Or ; also verses 16, 17
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'then on the day when he assigns his possessions as an inheritance
        to his sons, he may not treat the son of the loved as the firstborn in preference
        to the son of the unloved, who is the firstborn, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: A Rebellious Son'
      title: A Rebellious Son
      number: 17
      content: 'but he shall acknowledge the firstborn, the son of the unloved, by
        giving him a double portion of all that he has, for he is the firstfruits
        of his strength. The right of the firstborn is his.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CIf a man has a stubborn and rebellious son who will not obey
        the voice of his father or the voice of his mother, and, though they discipline
        him, will not listen to them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'then his father and his mother shall take hold of him and bring him
        out to the elders of his city at the gate of the place where he lives, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "and they shall say to the elders of his city, \u2018This our son
        is stubborn and rebellious; he will not obey our voice; he is a glutton and
        a drunkard.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: A Man Hanged on a Tree Is Cursed'
      title: A Man Hanged on a Tree Is Cursed
      number: 21
      content: 'Then all the men of the city shall stone him to death with stones.
        So you shall purge the evil from your midst, and all Israel shall hear, and
        fear.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CAnd if a man has committed a crime punishable by death and
        he is put to death, and you hang him on a tree, "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: his body shall not remain all night on the tree, but you shall bury
        him the same day, for a hanged man is cursed by God. You shall not defile
        your land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is giving you for
        an inheritance.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Various Laws'
      title: Various Laws
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CYou shall not see your brother\u2019s ox or his sheep going
        astray and ignore them. You shall take them back to your brother. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And if he does not live near you and you do not know who he is, you
        shall bring it home to your house, and it shall stay with you until your
        brother seeks it. Then you shall restore it to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And you shall do the same with his donkey or with his garment, or
        with any lost thing of your brother\u2019s, which he loses and you find;
        you may not ignore it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "You shall not see your brother\u2019s donkey or his ox fallen down
        by the way and ignore them. You shall help him to lift them up again.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CA woman shall not wear a man\u2019s garment, nor shall a man
        put on a woman\u2019s cloak, for whoever does these things is an abomination
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CIf you come across a bird\u2019s nest in any tree or on the
        ground, with young ones or eggs and the mother sitting on the young or on
        the eggs, you shall not take the mother with the young. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'You shall let the mother go, but the young you may take for yourself,
        that it may go well with you, and that you may live long.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CWhen you build a new house, you shall make a parapet for your
        roof, that you may not bring the guilt of blood upon your house, if anyone
        should fall from it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "  \u201CYou shall not sow your vineyard with two kinds of seed, lest
        the whole yield be forfeited,[[COMMENT(0)]] the crop that you have sown and
        the yield of the vineyard. "
      comments:
      - number: '22:9 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'You shall not plow with an ox and a donkey together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'You shall not wear cloth of wool and linen mixed together.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Laws Concerning Sexual Immorality'
      title: Laws Concerning Sexual Immorality
      number: 12
      content: "  \u201CYou shall make yourself tassels on the four corners of the
        garment with which you cover yourself.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CIf any man takes a wife and goes in to her and then hates her "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "and accuses her of misconduct and brings a bad name upon her, saying,
        \u2018I took this woman, and when I came near her, I did not find in her
        evidence of virginity,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'then the father of the young woman and her mother shall take and
        bring out the evidence of her virginity to the elders of the city in the
        gate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And the father of the young woman shall say to the elders, \u2018I
        gave my daughter to this man to marry, and he hates her; "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "and behold, he has accused her of misconduct, saying, \u201CI did
        not find in your daughter evidence of virginity.\u201D And yet this is the
        evidence of my daughter\u2019s virginity.\u2019 And they shall spread the
        cloak before the elders of the city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then the elders of that city shall take the man and whip[[COMMENT(0)]]
        him, '
      comments:
      - number: '22:18 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'and they shall fine him a hundred shekels[[COMMENT(0)]] of silver
        and give them to the father of the young woman, because he has brought a
        bad name upon a virgin of Israel. And she shall be his wife. He may not divorce
        her all his days. '
      comments:
      - number: '22:19 '
        content: 'A was about 2/5 ounce or 11 gramsOr   '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But if the thing is true, that evidence of virginity was not found
        in the young woman, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "then they shall bring out the young woman to the door of her father\u2019s
        house, and the men of her city shall stone her to death with stones, because
        she has done an outrageous thing in Israel by whoring in her father\u2019s
        house. So you shall purge the evil from your midst.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "  \u201CIf a man is found lying with the wife of another man, both
        of them shall die, the man who lay with the woman, and the woman. So you
        shall purge the evil from Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CIf there is a betrothed virgin, and a man meets her in the
        city and lies with her, "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "then you shall bring them both out to the gate of that city, and
        you shall stone them to death with stones, the young woman because she did
        not cry for help though she was in the city, and the man because he violated
        his neighbor\u2019s wife. So you shall purge the evil from your midst.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CBut if in the open country a man meets a young woman who is
        betrothed, and the man seizes her and lies with her, then only the man who
        lay with her shall die. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'But you shall do nothing to the young woman; she has committed no
        offense punishable by death. For this case is like that of a man attacking
        and murdering his neighbor, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'because he met her in the open country, and though the betrothed
        young woman cried for help there was no one to rescue her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "  \u201CIf a man meets a virgin who is not betrothed, and seizes
        her and lies with her, and they are found, "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'then the man who lay with her shall give to the father of the young
        woman fifty shekels of silver, and she shall be his wife, because he has
        violated her. He may not divorce her all his days.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "  [[COMMENT(0)]]  \u201CA man shall not take his father\u2019s wife,
        so that he does not uncover his father\u2019s nakedness."
      comments:
      - number: '22:30 '
        content: '  Ch 23:1 in Hebrew  Hebrew '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Those Excluded from the Assembly'
      title: Those Excluded from the Assembly
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CNo one whose testicles are crushed or whose male organ is
        cut off shall enter the assembly of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "  \u201CNo one born of a forbidden union may enter the assembly of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. Even to the tenth generation, none of his
        descendants may enter the assembly of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "  \u201CNo Ammonite or Moabite may enter the assembly of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        Even to the tenth generation, none of them may enter the assembly of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> forever, "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'because they did not meet you with bread and with water on the way,
        when you came out of Egypt, and because they hired against you Balaam the
        son of Beor from Pethor of Mesopotamia, to curse you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God would not listen to
        Balaam; instead the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God turned the curse
        into a blessing for you, because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God
        loved you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You shall not seek their peace or their prosperity all your days
        forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CYou shall not abhor an Edomite, for he is your brother. You
        shall not abhor an Egyptian, because you were a sojourner in his land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Uncleanness in the Camp'
      title: Uncleanness in the Camp
      number: 8
      content: 'Children born to them in the third generation may enter the assembly
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CWhen you are encamped against your enemies, then you shall
        keep yourself from every evil thing.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CIf any man among you becomes unclean because of a nocturnal
        emission, then he shall go outside the camp. He shall not come inside the
        camp, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'but when evening comes, he shall bathe himself in water, and as the
        sun sets, he may come inside the camp.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CYou shall have a place outside the camp, and you shall go out
        to it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And you shall have a trowel with your tools, and when you sit down
        outside, you shall dig a hole with it and turn back and cover up your excrement. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Miscellaneous Laws'
      title: Miscellaneous Laws
      number: 14
      content: 'Because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God walks in the midst
        of your camp, to deliver you and to give up your enemies before you, therefore
        your camp must be holy, so that he may not see anything indecent among you
        and turn away from you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "  \u201CYou shall not give up to his master a slave[[COMMENT(0)]]
        who has escaped from his master to you. "
      comments:
      - number: '23:15 '
        content: Or ; the Hebrew term designates a range of social and economic roles
          (see Preface)
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He shall dwell with you, in your midst, in the place that he shall
        choose within one of your towns, wherever it suits him. You shall not wrong
        him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CNone of the daughters of Israel shall be a cult prostitute,
        and none of the sons of Israel shall be a cult prostitute. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'You shall not bring the fee of a prostitute or the wages of a dog[[COMMENT(0)]]
        into the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God in payment for
        any vow, for both of these are an abomination to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God.  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:18 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "  \u201CYou shall not charge interest on loans to your brother, interest
        on money, interest on food, interest on anything that is lent for interest. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'You may charge a foreigner interest, but you may not charge your
        brother interest, that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God may bless
        you in all that you undertake in the land that you are entering to take possession
        of it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "  \u201CIf you make a vow to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God, you shall not delay fulfilling it, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God will surely require it of you, and you will be guilty of sin. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But if you refrain from vowing, you will not be guilty of sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'You shall be careful to do what has passed your lips, for you have
        voluntarily vowed to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God what you have
        promised with your mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CIf you go into your neighbor\u2019s vineyard, you may eat your
        fill of grapes, as many as you wish, but you shall not put any in your bag. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "If you go into your neighbor\u2019s standing grain, you may pluck
        the ears with your hand, but you shall not put a sickle to your neighbor\u2019s
        standing grain."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Laws Concerning Divorce'
      title: Laws Concerning Divorce
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CWhen a man takes a wife and marries her, if then she finds
        no favor in his eyes because he has found some indecency in her, and he writes
        her a certificate of divorce and puts it in her hand and sends her out of
        his house, and she departs out of his house, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "and if she goes and becomes another man\u2019s wife, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and the latter man hates her and writes her a certificate of divorce
        and puts it in her hand and sends her out of his house, or if the latter
        man dies, who took her to be his wife, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Miscellaneous Laws'
      title: Miscellaneous Laws
      number: 4
      content: 'then her former husband, who sent her away, may not take her again
        to be his wife, after she has been defiled, for that is an abomination before
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. And you shall not bring sin upon the land
        that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is giving you for an inheritance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "  \u201CWhen a man is newly married, he shall not go out with the
        army or be liable for any other public duty. He shall be free at home one
        year to be happy with his wife[[COMMENT(0)]] whom he has taken.  "
      comments:
      - number: '24:5 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CNo one shall take a mill or an upper millstone in pledge, for
        that would be taking a life in pledge.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "  \u201CIf a man is found stealing one of his brothers of the people
        of Israel, and if he treats him as a slave or sells him, then that thief
        shall die. So you shall purge the evil from your midst.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CTake care, in a case of leprous[[COMMENT(0)]] disease, to be
        very careful to do according to all that the Levitical priests shall direct
        you. As I commanded them, so you shall be careful to do. "
      comments:
      - number: '24:8 '
        content: was a term for several skin diseases; see Leviticus 13
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Remember what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God did to Miriam
        on the way as you came out of Egypt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CWhen you make your neighbor a loan of any sort, you shall not
        go into his house to collect his pledge. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'You shall stand outside, and the man to whom you make the loan shall
        bring the pledge out to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And if he is a poor man, you shall not sleep in his pledge. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'You shall restore to him the pledge as the sun sets, that he may
        sleep in his cloak and bless you. And it shall be righteousness for you before
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CYou shall not oppress a hired worker who is poor and needy,
        whether he is one of your brothers or one of the sojourners who are in your
        land within your towns. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'You shall give him his wages on the same day, before the sun sets
        (for he is poor and counts on it), lest he cry against you to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and you be guilty of sin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  \u201CFathers shall not be put to death because of their children,
        nor shall children be put to death because of their fathers. Each one shall
        be put to death for his own sin.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "  \u201CYou shall not pervert the justice due to the sojourner or
        to the fatherless, or take a widow\u2019s garment in pledge, "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'but you shall remember that you were a slave in Egypt and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God redeemed you from there; therefore I command you to do this.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "  \u201CWhen you reap your harvest in your field and forget a sheaf
        in the field, you shall not go back to get it. It shall be for the sojourner,
        the fatherless, and the widow, that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God may bless you in all the work of your hands. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'When you beat your olive trees, you shall not go over them again.
        It shall be for the sojourner, the fatherless, and the widow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'When you gather the grapes of your vineyard, you shall not strip
        it afterward. It shall be for the sojourner, the fatherless, and the widow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: You shall remember that you were a slave in the land of Egypt; therefore
        I command you to do this.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CIf there is a dispute between men and they come into court
        and the judges decide between them, acquitting the innocent and condemning
        the guilty, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'then if the guilty man deserves to be beaten, the judge shall cause
        him to lie down and be beaten in his presence with a number of stripes in
        proportion to his offense. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Forty stripes may be given him, but not more, lest, if one should
        go on to beat him with more stripes than these, your brother be degraded
        in your sight.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Laws Concerning Levirate Marriage'
      title: Laws Concerning Levirate Marriage
      number: 4
      content: "  \u201CYou shall not muzzle an ox when it is treading out the grain.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "  \u201CIf brothers dwell together, and one of them dies and has
        no son, the wife of the dead man shall not be married outside the family
        to a stranger. Her husband\u2019s brother shall go in to her and take her
        as his wife and perform the duty of a husband\u2019s brother to her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the first son whom she bears shall succeed to the name of his
        dead brother, that his name may not be blotted out of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And if the man does not wish to take his brother\u2019s wife, then
        his brother\u2019s wife shall go up to the gate to the elders and say, \u2018My
        husband\u2019s brother refuses to perpetuate his brother\u2019s name in Israel;
        he will not perform the duty of a husband\u2019s brother to me.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then the elders of his city shall call him and speak to him, and
        if he persists, saying, \u2018I do not wish to take her,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "then his brother\u2019s wife shall go up to him in the presence of
        the elders and pull his sandal off his foot and spit in his face. And she
        shall answer and say, \u2018So shall it be done to the man who does not build
        up his brother\u2019s house.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Miscellaneous Laws'
      title: Miscellaneous Laws
      number: 10
      content: "And the name of his house[[COMMENT(0)]] shall be called in Israel,
        \u2018The house of him who had his sandal pulled off.\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '25:10 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CWhen men fight with one another and the wife of the one draws
        near to rescue her husband from the hand of him who is beating him and puts
        out her hand and seizes him by the private parts, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'then you shall cut off her hand. Your eye shall have no pity.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CYou shall not have in your bag two kinds of weights, a large
        and a small. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'You shall not have in your house two kinds of measures, a large and
        a small. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'A full and fair[[COMMENT(0)]] weight you shall have, a full and fair
        measure you shall have, that your days may be long in the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God is giving you. '
      comments:
      - number: '25:15 '
        content: Or , or ; twice in this verse
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For all who do such things, all who act dishonestly, are an abomination
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "  \u201CRemember what Amalek did to you on the way as you came out
        of Egypt, "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'how he attacked you on the way when you were faint and weary, and
        cut off your tail, those who were lagging behind you, and he did not fear
        God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Therefore when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has given
        you rest from all your enemies around you, in the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God is giving you for an inheritance to possess, you shall blot out
        the memory of Amalek from under heaven; you shall not forget.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Offerings of Firstfruits and Tithes'
      title: Offerings of Firstfruits and Tithes
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CWhen you come into the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God is giving you for an inheritance and have taken possession of it
        and live in it, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'you shall take some of the first of all the fruit of the ground,
        which you harvest from your land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God is giving you, and you shall put it in a basket, and you shall go to
        the place that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will choose, to make
        his name to dwell there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And you shall go to the priest who is in office at that time and
        say to him, \u2018I declare today to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God that I have come into the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> swore
        to our fathers to give us.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then the priest shall take the basket from your hand and set it down
        before the altar of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CAnd you shall make response before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, \u2018A wandering Aramean was my father. And he went down into
        Egypt and sojourned there, few in number, and there he became a nation, great,
        mighty, and populous. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the Egyptians treated us harshly and humiliated us and laid on
        us hard labor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then we cried to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of our
        fathers, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> heard our voice and saw our
        affliction, our toil, and our oppression. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> brought us out of Egypt with
        a mighty hand and an outstretched arm, with great deeds of terror,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        with signs and wonders. '
      comments:
      - number: '26:8 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And he brought us into this place and gave us this land, a land flowing
        with milk and honey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And behold, now I bring the first of the fruit of the ground, which
        you, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have given me.\u2019 And you shall set
        it down before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God and worship before
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And you shall rejoice in all the good that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God has given to you and to your house, you, and the Levite, and the
        sojourner who is among you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CWhen you have finished paying all the tithe of your produce
        in the third year, which is the year of tithing, giving it to the Levite,
        the sojourner, the fatherless, and the widow, so that they may eat within
        your towns and be filled, "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "then you shall say before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God,
        \u2018I have removed the sacred portion out of my house, and moreover, I
        have given it to the Levite, the sojourner, the fatherless, and the widow,
        according to all your commandment that you have commanded me. I have not
        transgressed any of your commandments, nor have I forgotten them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I have not eaten of the tithe while I was mourning, or removed any
        of it while I was unclean, or offered any of it to the dead. I have obeyed
        the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> my God. I have done according
        to all that you have commanded me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Look down from your holy habitation, from heaven, and bless your
        people Israel and the ground that you have given us, as you swore to our
        fathers, a land flowing with milk and honey.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CThis day the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God commands
        you to do these statutes and rules. You shall therefore be careful to do
        them with all your heart and with all your soul. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'You have declared today that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is your
        God, and that you will walk in his ways, and keep his statutes and his commandments
        and his rules, and will obey his voice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has declared today that you are
        a people for his treasured possession, as he has promised you, and that you
        are to keep all his commandments, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "and that he will set you in praise and in fame and in honor high
        above all nations that he has made, and that you shall be a people holy to
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, as he promised.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Altar on Mount Ebal'
      title: The Altar on Mount Ebal
      number: 1
      content: "  Now Moses and the elders of Israel commanded the people, saying,
        \u201CKeep the whole commandment that I command you today. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And on the day you cross over the Jordan to the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God is giving you, you shall set up large stones and plaster them with
        plaster. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And you shall write on them all the words of this law, when you cross
        over to enter the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is giving
        you, a land flowing with milk and honey, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of your fathers, has promised you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And when you have crossed over the Jordan, you shall set up these
        stones, concerning which I command you today, on Mount Ebal, and you shall
        plaster them with plaster. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And there you shall build an altar to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, an altar of stones. You shall wield no iron tool on them; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'you shall build an altar to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God of uncut[[COMMENT(0)]] stones. And you shall offer burnt offerings on
        it to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, '
      comments:
      - number: '27:6 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and you shall sacrifice peace offerings and shall eat there, and
        you shall rejoice before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Curses from Mount Ebal'
      title: Curses from Mount Ebal
      number: 8
      content: "And you shall write on the stones all the words of this law very
        plainly.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Moses and the Levitical priests said to all Israel, \u201CKeep
        silence and hear, O Israel: this day you have become the people of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "You shall therefore obey the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, keeping his commandments and his statutes, which I command you
        today.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'That day Moses charged the people, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CWhen you have crossed over the Jordan, these shall stand on
        Mount Gerizim to bless the people: Simeon, Levi, Judah, Issachar, Joseph,
        and Benjamin. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And these shall stand on Mount Ebal for the curse: Reuben, Gad, Asher,
        Zebulun, Dan, and Naphtali. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And the Levites shall declare to all the men of Israel in a loud
        voice:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "  \u201C\u2018Cursed be the man who makes a carved or cast metal
        image, an abomination to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, a thing made by
        the hands of a craftsman, and sets it up in secret.\u2019 And all the people
        shall answer and say, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  \u201C\u2018Cursed be anyone who dishonors his father or his mother.\u2019
        And all the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "  \u201C\u2018Cursed be anyone who moves his neighbor\u2019s landmark.\u2019
        And all the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "  \u201C\u2018Cursed be anyone who misleads a blind man on the road.\u2019
        And all the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "  \u201C\u2018Cursed be anyone who perverts the justice due to the
        sojourner, the fatherless, and the widow.\u2019 And all the people shall
        say, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "  \u201C\u2018Cursed be anyone who lies with his father\u2019s wife,
        because he has uncovered his father\u2019s nakedness.\u2019[[COMMENT(0)]]
        And all the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '27:20 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "  \u201C\u2018Cursed be anyone who lies with any kind of animal.\u2019
        And all the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "  \u201C\u2018Cursed be anyone who lies with his sister, whether
        the daughter of his father or the daughter of his mother.\u2019 And all the
        people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "  \u201C\u2018Cursed be anyone who lies with his mother-in-law.\u2019
        And all the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "  \u201C\u2018Cursed be anyone who strikes down his neighbor in secret.\u2019
        And all the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "  \u201C\u2018Cursed be anyone who takes a bribe to shed innocent
        blood.\u2019 And all the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "  \u201C\u2018Cursed be anyone who does not confirm the words of
        this law by doing them.\u2019 And all the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Blessings for Obedience'
      title: Blessings for Obedience
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CAnd if you faithfully obey the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, being careful to do all his commandments that I command you today,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will set you high above all the
        nations of the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And all these blessings shall come upon you and overtake you, if
        you obey the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Blessed shall you be in the city, and blessed shall you be in the
        field. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Blessed shall be the fruit of your womb and the fruit of your ground
        and the fruit of your cattle, the increase of your herds and the young of
        your flock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Blessed shall be your basket and your kneading bowl. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Blessed shall you be when you come in, and blessed shall you be when
        you go out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  will cause your enemies who
        rise against you to be defeated before you. They shall come out against you
        one way and flee before you seven ways. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  will command the blessing on you
        in your barns and in all that you undertake. And he will bless you in the
        land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is giving you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will establish you as a people holy
        to himself, as he has sworn to you, if you keep the commandments of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God and walk in his ways. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And all the peoples of the earth shall see that you are called by
        the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and they shall be afraid of
        you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will make you abound in prosperity,
        in the fruit of your womb and in the fruit of your livestock and in the fruit
        of your ground, within the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> swore
        to your fathers to give you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will open to you his good treasury,
        the heavens, to give the rain to your land in its season and to bless all
        the work of your hands. And you shall lend to many nations, but you shall
        not borrow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will make you the head and not
        the tail, and you shall only go up and not down, if you obey the commandments
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, which I command you today, being
        careful to do them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Curses for Disobedience'
      title: Curses for Disobedience
      number: 14
      content: 'and if you do not turn aside from any of the words that I command
        you today, to the right hand or to the left, to go after other gods to serve
        them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CBut if you will not obey the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God or be careful to do all his commandments and his statutes that I
        command you today, then all these curses shall come upon you and overtake
        you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Cursed shall you be in the city, and cursed shall you be in the field. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Cursed shall be your basket and your kneading bowl. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Cursed shall be the fruit of your womb and the fruit of your ground,
        the increase of your herds and the young of your flock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Cursed shall you be when you come in, and cursed shall you be when
        you go out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  will send on you curses, confusion,
        and frustration in all that you undertake to do, until you are destroyed
        and perish quickly on account of the evil of your deeds, because you have
        forsaken me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will make the pestilence stick to
        you until he has consumed you off the land that you are entering to take
        possession of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will strike you with wasting disease
        and with fever, inflammation and fiery heat, and with drought[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and with blight and with mildew. They shall pursue you until you perish. '
      comments:
      - number: '28:22 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And the heavens over your head shall be bronze, and the earth under
        you shall be iron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will make the rain of your land powder.
        From heaven dust shall come down on you until you are destroyed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "  \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will cause you to be defeated
        before your enemies. You shall go out one way against them and flee seven
        ways before them. And you shall be a horror to all the kingdoms of the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And your dead body shall be food for all birds of the air and for
        the beasts of the earth, and there shall be no one to frighten them away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will strike you with the boils of
        Egypt, and with tumors and scabs and itch, of which you cannot be healed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will strike you with madness and
        blindness and confusion of mind, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'and you shall grope at noonday, as the blind grope in darkness, and
        you shall not prosper in your ways.[[COMMENT(0)]] And you shall be only oppressed
        and robbed continually, and there shall be no one to help you. '
      comments:
      - number: '28:29 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'You shall betroth a wife, but another man shall ravish her. You shall
        build a house, but you shall not dwell in it. You shall plant a vineyard,
        but you shall not enjoy its fruit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Your ox shall be slaughtered before your eyes, but you shall not
        eat any of it. Your donkey shall be seized before your face, but shall not
        be restored to you. Your sheep shall be given to your enemies, but there
        shall be no one to help you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Your sons and your daughters shall be given to another people, while
        your eyes look on and fail with longing for them all day long, but you shall
        be helpless. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'A nation that you have not known shall eat up the fruit of your ground
        and of all your labors, and you shall be only oppressed and crushed continually, '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'so that you are driven mad by the sights that your eyes see. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will strike you on the knees and
        on the legs with grievous boils of which you cannot be healed, from the sole
        of your foot to the crown of your head.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will bring you and your king
        whom you set over you to a nation that neither you nor your fathers have
        known. And there you shall serve other gods of wood and stone. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'And you shall become a horror, a proverb, and a byword among all
        the peoples where the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will lead you away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'You shall carry much seed into the field and shall gather in little,
        for the locust shall consume it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'You shall plant vineyards and dress them, but you shall neither drink
        of the wine nor gather the grapes, for the worm shall eat them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'You shall have olive trees throughout all your territory, but you
        shall not anoint yourself with the oil, for your olives shall drop off. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'You shall father sons and daughters, but they shall not be yours,
        for they shall go into captivity. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'The cricket[[COMMENT(0)]] shall possess all your trees and the fruit
        of your ground. '
      comments:
      - number: '28:42 '
        content: Identity uncertain
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'The sojourner who is among you shall rise higher and higher above
        you, and you shall come down lower and lower. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'He shall lend to you, and you shall not lend to him. He shall be
        the head, and you shall be the tail.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "  \u201CAll these curses shall come upon you and pursue you and overtake
        you till you are destroyed, because you did not obey the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, to keep his commandments and his statutes that he commanded you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'They shall be a sign and a wonder against you and your offspring
        forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'Because you did not serve the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God
        with joyfulness and gladness of heart, because of the abundance of all things, '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'therefore you shall serve your enemies whom the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will send against you, in hunger and thirst, in nakedness, and lacking everything.
        And he will put a yoke of iron on your neck until he has destroyed you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will bring a nation against you from
        far away, from the end of the earth, swooping down like the eagle, a nation
        whose language you do not understand, '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'a hard-faced nation who shall not respect the old or show mercy to
        the young. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'It shall eat the offspring of your cattle and the fruit of your ground,
        until you are destroyed; it also shall not leave you grain, wine, or oil,
        the increase of your herds or the young of your flock, until they have caused
        you to perish.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "\u201CThey shall besiege you in all your towns, until your high and
        fortified walls, in which you trusted, come down throughout all your land.
        And they shall besiege you in all your towns throughout all your land, which
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has given you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'And you shall eat the fruit of your womb, the flesh of your sons
        and daughters, whom the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has given you,
        in the siege and in the distress with which your enemies shall distress you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'The man who is the most tender and refined among you will begrudge
        food to his brother, to the wife he embraces,[[COMMENT(0)]] and to the last
        of the children whom he has left, '
      comments:
      - number: '28:54 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'so that he will not give to any of them any of the flesh of his children
        whom he is eating, because he has nothing else left, in the siege and in
        the distress with which your enemy shall distress you in all your towns. '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'The most tender and refined woman among you, who would not venture
        to set the sole of her foot on the ground because she is so delicate and
        tender, will begrudge to the husband she embraces,[[COMMENT(0)]] to her son
        and to her daughter, '
      comments:
      - number: '28:56 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: 'her afterbirth that comes out from between her feet and her children
        whom she bears, because lacking everything she will eat them secretly, in
        the siege and in the distress with which your enemy shall distress you in
        your towns.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: "\u201CIf you are not careful to do all the words of this law that
        are written in this book, that you may fear this glorious and awesome name,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, "
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will bring on you and your offspring
        extraordinary afflictions, afflictions severe and lasting, and sicknesses
        grievous and lasting. '
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: 'And he will bring upon you again all the diseases of Egypt, of which
        you were afraid, and they shall cling to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: 'Every sickness also and every affliction that is not recorded in
        the book of this law, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will bring upon you,
        until you are destroyed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: 'Whereas you were as numerous as the stars of heaven, you shall be
        left few in number, because you did not obey the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: 'And as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  took delight in doing you
        good and multiplying you, so the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will take delight
        in bringing ruin upon you and destroying you. And you shall be plucked off
        the land that you are entering to take possession of it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: "\u201CAnd the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  will scatter you among
        all peoples, from one end of the earth to the other, and there you shall
        serve other gods of wood and stone, which neither you nor your fathers have
        known. "
      comments: []
    - name: '65: '
      title: 
      number: 65
      content: 'And among these nations you shall find no respite, and there shall
        be no resting place for the sole of your foot, but the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will give you there a trembling heart and failing eyes and a languishing
        soul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: 'Your life shall hang in doubt before you. Night and day you shall
        be in dread and have no assurance of your life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '67: '
      title: 
      number: 67
      content: "In the morning you shall say, \u2018If only it were evening!\u2019
        and at evening you shall say, \u2018If only it were morning!\u2019 because
        of the dread that your heart shall feel, and the sights that your eyes shall
        see. "
      comments: []
    - name: '68: '
      title: 
      number: 68
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  will bring you back in ships
        to Egypt, a journey that I promised that you should never make again; and
        there you shall offer yourselves for sale to your enemies as male and female
        slaves, but there will be no buyer.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Covenant Renewed in Moab'
      title: The Covenant Renewed in Moab
      number: 1
      content: '    [[COMMENT(0)]] These are the words of the covenant that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        commanded Moses to make with the people of Israel in the land of Moab, besides
        the covenant that he had made with them at Horeb.  '
      comments:
      - number: '29:1 '
        content: '  Ch 28:69 in Hebrew    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "  [[COMMENT(0)]] And Moses summoned all Israel and said to them:
        \u201CYou have seen all that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> did before your
        eyes in the land of Egypt, to Pharaoh and to all his servants and to all
        his land, "
      comments:
      - number: '29:2 '
        content: '  Ch 29:1 in Hebrew  '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'the great trials that your eyes saw, the signs, and those great wonders. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But to this day the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has not given you
        a heart to understand or eyes to see or ears to hear. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I have led you forty years in the wilderness. Your clothes have not
        worn out on you, and your sandals have not worn off your feet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You have not eaten bread, and you have not drunk wine or strong drink,
        that you may know that I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And when you came to this place, Sihon the king of Heshbon and Og
        the king of Bashan came out against us to battle, but we defeated them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'We took their land and gave it for an inheritance to the Reubenites,
        the Gadites, and the half-tribe of the Manassites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Therefore keep the words of this covenant and do them, that you may
        prosper[[COMMENT(0)]] in all that you do.  '
      comments:
      - number: '29:9 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CYou are standing today, all of you, before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God: the heads of your tribes,[[COMMENT(0)]] your elders, and your officers,
        all the men of Israel, "
      comments:
      - number: '29:10 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Syriac; Hebrew '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'your little ones, your wives, and the sojourner who is in your camp,
        from the one who chops your wood to the one who draws your water, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'so that you may enter into the sworn covenant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is making with you
        today, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'that he may establish you today as his people, and that he may be
        your God, as he promised you, and as he swore to your fathers, to Abraham,
        to Isaac, and to Jacob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'It is not with you alone that I am making this sworn covenant, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'but with whoever is standing here with us today before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God, and with whoever is not here with us today.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CYou know how we lived in the land of Egypt, and how we came
        through the midst of the nations through which you passed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And you have seen their detestable things, their idols of wood and
        stone, of silver and gold, which were among them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Beware lest there be among you a man or woman or clan or tribe whose
        heart is turning away today from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God
        to go and serve the gods of those nations. Beware lest there be among you
        a root bearing poisonous and bitter fruit, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "one who, when he hears the words of this sworn covenant, blesses
        himself in his heart, saying, \u2018I shall be safe, though I walk in the
        stubbornness of my heart.\u2019 This will lead to the sweeping away of moist
        and dry alike. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will not be willing to forgive him,
        but rather the anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and his jealousy
        will smoke against that man, and the curses written in this book will settle
        upon him, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  will blot out his name from
        under heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will single him out from all
        the tribes of Israel for calamity, in accordance with all the curses of the
        covenant written in this Book of the Law. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And the next generation, your children who rise up after you, and
        the foreigner who comes from a far land, will say, when they see the afflictions
        of that land and the sicknesses with which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has made it sick\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "the whole land burned out with brimstone and salt, nothing sown and
        nothing growing, where no plant can sprout, an overthrow like that of Sodom
        and Gomorrah, Admah, and Zeboiim, which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> overthrew
        in his anger and wrath\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "all the nations will say, \u2018Why has the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        done thus to this land? What caused the heat of this great anger?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then people will say, \u2018It is because they abandoned the covenant
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of their fathers, which he made
        with them when he brought them out of the land of Egypt, "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'and went and served other gods and worshiped them, gods whom they
        had not known and whom he had not allotted to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Therefore the anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was kindled
        against this land, bringing upon it all the curses written in this book, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  uprooted them from their land
        in anger and fury and great wrath, and cast them into another land, as they
        are this day.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CThe secret things belong to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God, but the things that are revealed belong to us and to our children
        forever, that we may do all the words of this law."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Repentance and Forgiveness'
      title: Repentance and Forgiveness
      number: 1
      content: "    \u201CAnd when all these things come upon you, the blessing and
        the curse, which I have set before you, and you call them to mind among all
        the nations where the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has driven you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and return to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, you and your
        children, and obey his voice in all that I command you today, with all your
        heart and with all your soul, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will restore your fortunes
        and have mercy on you, and he will gather you again from all the peoples
        where the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has scattered you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'If your outcasts are in the uttermost parts of heaven, from there
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will gather you, and from there
        he will take you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will bring you into
        the land that your fathers possessed, that you may possess it. And he will
        make you more prosperous and numerous than your fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will circumcise your
        heart and the heart of your offspring, so that you will love the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God with all your heart and with all your soul, that you may live. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will put all these curses
        on your foes and enemies who persecuted you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And you shall again obey the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and keep all his commandments that I command you today. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will make you abundantly
        prosperous in all the work of your hand, in the fruit of your womb and in
        the fruit of your cattle and in the fruit of your ground. For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will again take delight in prospering you, as he took delight in your fathers, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The Choice of Life and Death'
      title: The Choice of Life and Death
      number: 10
      content: 'when you obey the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God,
        to keep his commandments and his statutes that are written in this Book of
        the Law, when you turn to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God with all
        your heart and with all your soul.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CFor this commandment that I command you today is not too hard
        for you, neither is it far off. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "It is not in heaven, that you should say, \u2018Who will ascend to
        heaven for us and bring it to us, that we may hear it and do it?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Neither is it beyond the sea, that you should say, \u2018Who will
        go over the sea for us and bring it to us, that we may hear it and do it?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But the word is very near you. It is in your mouth and in your heart,
        so that you can do it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CSee, I have set before you today life and good, death and evil. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'If you obey the commandments of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God[[COMMENT(0)]] that I command you today, by loving the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, by walking in his ways, and by keeping his commandments and his
        statutes and his rules, then you shall live and multiply, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God will bless you in the land that you are entering to take possession
        of it. '
      comments:
      - number: '30:16 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew lacks <span class="ChapterContent_bdit___RrVH">Lord</span> 
          Or '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But if your heart turns away, and you will not hear, but are drawn
        away to worship other gods and serve them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'I declare to you today, that you shall surely perish. You shall not
        live long in the land that you are going over the Jordan to enter and possess. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'I call heaven and earth to witness against you today, that I have
        set before you life and death, blessing and curse. Therefore choose life,
        that you and your offspring may live, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "loving the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, obeying his voice
        and holding fast to him, for he is your life and length of days, that you
        may dwell in the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> swore to your
        fathers, to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob, to give them.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Joshua to Succeed Moses'
      title: Joshua to Succeed Moses
      number: 1
      content: '  So Moses continued to speak these words to all Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he said to them, \u201CI am 120 years old today. I am no longer
        able to go out and come in. The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has said to me,
        \u2018You shall not go over this Jordan.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God himself will go over before
        you. He will destroy these nations before you, so that you shall dispossess
        them, and Joshua will go over at your head, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has spoken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will do to them as he did to
        Sihon and Og, the kings of the Amorites, and to their land, when he destroyed
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will give them over to you, and
        you shall do to them according to the whole commandment that I have commanded
        you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Be strong and courageous. Do not fear or be in dread of them, for
        it is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God who goes with you. He will
        not leave you or forsake you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then Moses summoned Joshua and said to him in the sight of all Israel,
        \u201CBe strong and courageous, for you shall go with this people into the
        land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has sworn to their fathers to give
        them, and you shall put them in possession of it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: The Reading of the Law'
      title: The Reading of the Law
      number: 8
      content: "It is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  who goes before you. He will
        be with you; he will not leave you or forsake you. Do not fear or be dismayed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Moses wrote this law and gave it to the priests, the sons of
        Levi, who carried the ark of the covenant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and to all the elders of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Moses commanded them, \u201CAt the end of every seven years,
        at the set time in the year of release, at the Feast of Booths, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'when all Israel comes to appear before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God at the place that he will choose, you shall read this law before
        all Israel in their hearing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Assemble the people, men, women, and little ones, and the sojourner
        within your towns, that they may hear and learn to fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, and be careful to do all the words of this law, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Joshua Commissioned to Lead Israel'
      title: Joshua Commissioned to Lead Israel
      number: 13
      content: "and that their children, who have not known it, may hear and learn
        to fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, as long as you live in
        the land that you are going over the Jordan to possess.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, \u201CBehold,
        the days approach when you must die. Call Joshua and present yourselves in
        the tent of meeting, that I may commission him.\u201D And Moses and Joshua
        went and presented themselves in the tent of meeting. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> appeared in the tent in a pillar
        of cloud. And the pillar of cloud stood over the entrance of the tent.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, \u201CBehold,
        you are about to lie down with your fathers. Then this people will rise and
        whore after the foreign gods among them in the land that they are entering,
        and they will forsake me and break my covenant that I have made with them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then my anger will be kindled against them in that day, and I will
        forsake them and hide my face from them, and they will be devoured. And many
        evils and troubles will come upon them, so that they will say in that day,
        \u2018Have not these evils come upon us because our God is not among us?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And I will surely hide my face in that day because of all the evil
        that they have done, because they have turned to other gods.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CNow therefore write this song and teach it to the people of
        Israel. Put it in their mouths, that this song may be a witness for me against
        the people of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'For when I have brought them into the land flowing with milk and
        honey, which I swore to give to their fathers, and they have eaten and are
        full and grown fat, they will turn to other gods and serve them, and despise
        me and break my covenant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And when many evils and troubles have come upon them, this song shall
        confront them as a witness (for it will live unforgotten in the mouths of
        their offspring). For I know what they are inclined to do even today, before
        I have brought them into the land that I swore to give.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So Moses wrote this song the same day and taught it to the people
        of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "  And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>[[COMMENT(0)]] commissioned
        Joshua the son of Nun and said, \u201CBe strong and courageous, for you shall
        bring the people of Israel into the land that I swore to give them. I will
        be with you.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '31:23 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'When Moses had finished writing the words of this law in a book to
        the very end, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Moses commanded the Levites who carried the ark of the covenant of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CTake this Book of the Law and put it by the side of the ark
        of the covenant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, that it may
        be there for a witness against you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For I know how rebellious and stubborn you are. Behold, even today
        while I am yet alive with you, you have been rebellious against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        How much more after my death! '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Assemble to me all the elders of your tribes and your officers, that
        I may speak these words in their ears and call heaven and earth to witness
        against them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: The Song of Moses'
      title: The Song of Moses
      number: 29
      content: "For I know that after my death you will surely act corruptly and
        turn aside from the way that I have commanded you. And in the days to come
        evil will befall you, because you will do what is evil in the sight of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, provoking him to anger through the work of your
        hands.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Then Moses spoke the words of this song until they were finished,
        in the ears of all the assembly of Israel:'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CGive ear, O heavens, and I will speak,and let the earth hear
        the words of my mouth.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'May my teaching drop as the rain,my speech distill as the dew,like
        gentle rain upon the tender grass,and like showers upon the herb.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For I will proclaim the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;ascribe
        greatness to our God!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "  \u201CThe Rock, his work is perfect,for all his ways are justice.A
        God of faithfulness and without iniquity,just and upright is he.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They have dealt corruptly with him;they are no longer his children
        because they are blemished;they are a crooked and twisted generation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Do you thus repay the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,you foolish and
        senseless people?Is not he your father, who created you,who made you and
        established you?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  Remember the days of old;consider the years of many generations; 
        ask your father, and he will show you,your elders, and they will tell you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'When the Most High gave to the nations their inheritance,when he
        divided mankind,he fixed the borders[[COMMENT(0)]] of the peoplesaccording
        to the number of the sons of God.  '
      comments:
      - number: '32:8 '
        content: 'Or Compare Dead Sea Scroll, Septuagint; Masoretic Text '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s portion is his people,Jacob
        his allotted heritage.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CHe found him in a desert land,and in the howling waste of the
        wilderness;he encircled him, he cared for him,he kept him as the apple of
        his eye.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  Like an eagle that stirs up its nest,that flutters over its young,spreading
        out its wings, catching them,bearing them on its pinions,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> alone guided him,  no foreign god
        was with him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  He made him ride on the high places of the land,and he ate the
        produce of the field,and he suckled him with honey out of the rock,and oil
        out of the flinty rock.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Curds from the herd, and milk from the flock,with fat[[COMMENT(0)]]
        of lambs,rams of Bashan and goats,with the very finest of the wheat\u2014and
        you drank foaming wine made from the blood of the grape.  "
      comments:
      - number: '32:14 '
        content: 'That is, with the bestHebrew '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CBut Jeshurun grew fat, and kicked;  you grew fat, stout, and
        sleek;  then he forsook God who made himand scoffed at the Rock of his salvation.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  They stirred him to jealousy with strange gods;with abominations
        they provoked him to anger.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  They sacrificed to demons that were no gods,to gods they had never
        known,to new gods that had come recently,whom your fathers had never dreaded.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'You were unmindful of the Rock that bore[[COMMENT(0)]] you,and you
        forgot the God who gave you birth.  '
      comments:
      - number: '32:18 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "  \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> saw it and spurned them,because
        of the provocation of his sons and his daughters.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And he said, \u2018I will hide my face from them;I will see what
        their end will be,for they are a perverse generation,children in whom is
        no faithfulness.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  They have made me jealous with what is no god;they have provoked
        me to anger with their idols.So I will make them jealous with those who are
        no people;I will provoke them to anger with a foolish nation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For a fire is kindled by my anger,and it burns to the depths of Sheol,devours
        the earth and its increase,and sets on fire the foundations of the mountains.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201C\u2018And I will heap disasters upon them;  I will spend my
        arrows on them;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'they shall be wasted with hunger,and devoured by plagueand poisonous
        pestilence;I will send the teeth of beasts against them,with the venom of
        things that crawl in the dust.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  Outdoors the sword shall bereave,and indoors terror,for young man
        and woman alike,the nursing child with the man of gray hairs.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "  I would have said, \u201CI will cut them to pieces;  I will wipe
        them from human memory,\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "had I not feared provocation by the enemy,lest their adversaries
        should misunderstand,lest they should say, \u201COur hand is triumphant,it
        was not the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> who did all this.\u201D\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CFor they are a nation void of counsel,and there is no understanding
        in them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '  If they were wise, they would understand this;they would discern
        their latter end!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'How could one have chased a thousand,and two have put ten thousand
        to flight,unless their Rock had sold them,and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had given them up?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'For their rock is not as our Rock;  our enemies are by themselves.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'For their vine comes from the vine of Sodomand from the fields of
        Gomorrah;their grapes are grapes of poison;their clusters are bitter;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'their wine is the poison of serpentsand the cruel venom of asps.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "\u201C\u2018Is not this laid up in store with me,  sealed up in my
        treasuries?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "  Vengeance is mine, and recompense,[[COMMENT(0)]]  for the time
        when their foot shall slip;for the day of their calamity is at hand,and their
        doom comes swiftly.\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '32:35 '
        content: 'Septuagint '
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will vindicate[[COMMENT(0)]]
        his people  and have compassion on his servants,when he sees that their power
        is goneand there is none remaining, bond or free.  '
      comments:
      - number: '32:36 '
        content: 'Septuagint '
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Then he will say, \u2018Where are their gods,  the rock in which
        they took refuge,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'who ate the fat of their sacrificesand drank the wine of their drink
        offering?Let them rise up and help you;let them be your protection!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "\u201C\u2018See now that I, even I, am he,and there is no god beside
        me;  I kill and I make alive;  I wound and I heal;and there is none that
        can deliver out of my hand.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'For I lift up my hand to heavenand swear, As I live forever,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'if I sharpen my flashing sword[[COMMENT(0)]]and my hand takes hold
        on judgment,I will take vengeance on my adversariesand will repay those who
        hate me.  '
      comments:
      - number: '32:41 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "I will make my arrows drunk with blood,and my sword shall devour
        flesh\u2014with the blood of the slain and the captives,from the long-haired
        heads of the enemy.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "  \u201CRejoice with him, O heavens;[[COMMENT(0)]]bow down to him,
        all gods,for he avenges the blood of his childrenand takes vengeance on his
        adversaries.He repays those who hate himand cleanses his people\u2019s land.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '32:43 '
        content: 'Dead Sea Scroll, Septuagint; Masoretic Text Masoretic Text lacks
          Dead Sea Scroll, Septuagint; Masoretic Text Dead Sea Scroll, Septuagint;
          Masoretic Text lacks Or Septuagint, Vulgate; Hebrew '
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Moses came and recited all the words of this song in the hearing
        of the people, he and Joshua[[COMMENT(0)]] the son of Nun. '
      comments:
      - number: '32:44 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Syriac, Vulgate; Hebrew '
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'And when Moses had finished speaking all these words to all Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "he said to them, \u201CTake to heart all the words by which I am
        warning you today, that you may command them to your children, that they
        may be careful to do all the words of this law. "
      comments: []
    - name: "47: Moses\u2019 Death Foretold"
      title: "Moses\u2019 Death Foretold"
      number: 47
      content: "For it is no empty word for you, but your very life, and by this
        word you shall live long in the land that you are going over the Jordan to
        possess.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'That very day the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "\u201CGo up this mountain of the Abarim, Mount Nebo, which is in
        the land of Moab, opposite Jericho, and view the land of Canaan, which I
        am giving to the people of Israel for a possession. "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'And die on the mountain which you go up, and be gathered to your
        people, as Aaron your brother died in Mount Hor and was gathered to his people, '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'because you broke faith with me in the midst of the people of Israel
        at the waters of Meribah-kadesh, in the wilderness of Zin, and because you
        did not treat me as holy in the midst of the people of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "For you shall see the land before you, but you shall not go there,
        into the land that I am giving to the people of Israel.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Moses\u2019 Final Blessing on Israel"
      title: "Moses\u2019 Final Blessing on Israel"
      number: 1
      content: '  This is the blessing with which Moses the man of God blessed the
        people of Israel before his death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He said,  \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came from Sinaiand
        dawned from Seir upon us;[[COMMENT(0)]]he shone forth from Mount Paran;he
        came from the ten thousands of holy ones,with flaming fire at his right hand.  "
      comments:
      - number: '33:2 '
        content: Septuagint, Syriac, Vulgate; Hebrew The meaning of the Hebrew word
          is uncertain
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Yes, he loved his people,[[COMMENT(0)]]  all his holy ones were in
        his hand;  so they followed in your steps,receiving direction from you,  '
      comments:
      - number: '33:3 '
        content: Septuagint; Hebrew Hebrew The meaning of the Hebrew word is uncertain
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'when Moses commanded us a law,as a possession for the assembly of
        Jacob.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Thus the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>[[COMMENT(0)]]  became king in
        Jeshurun,when the heads of the people were gathered,all the tribes of Israel
        together.  '
      comments:
      - number: '33:5 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "  \u201CLet Reuben live, and not die,but let his men be few.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And this he said of Judah:\u201CHear, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the voice of Judah,and bring him in to his people.With your hands contend[[COMMENT(0)]]
        for him,and be a help against his adversaries.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '33:7 '
        content: 'Probable reading; Hebrew '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And of Levi he said,\u201CGive to Levi[[COMMENT(0)]]  your Thummim,and
        your Urim to your godly one,  whom you tested at Massah,with whom you quarreled
        at the waters of Meribah;  "
      comments:
      - number: '33:8 '
        content: 'Dead Sea Scroll, Septuagint; Masoretic Text lacks '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "who said of his father and mother,\u2018I regard them not\u2019; 
        he disowned his brothersand ignored his children.For they observed your wordand
        kept your covenant.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  They shall teach Jacob your rulesand Israel your law;  they shall
        put incense before youand whole burnt offerings on your altar.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Bless, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, his substance,and accept the
        work of his hands;crush the loins of his adversaries,of those who hate him,
        that they rise not again.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "  Of Benjamin he said,\u201CThe beloved of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        dwells in safety.The High God[[COMMENT(0)]] surrounds him all day long,and
        dwells between his shoulders.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '33:12 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And of Joseph he said,  \u201CBlessed by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        be his land,with the choicest gifts of heaven above,[[COMMENT(0)]]and of
        the deep that crouches beneath,  "
      comments:
      - number: '33:13 '
        content: 'Two Hebrew manuscripts and Targum; Hebrew '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'with the choicest fruits of the sunand the rich yield of the months,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'with the finest produce of the ancient mountainsand the abundance
        of the everlasting hills,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'with the best gifts of the earth and its fullnessand the favor of
        him who dwells in the bush.May these rest on the head of Joseph,on the pate
        of him who is prince among his brothers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "  A firstborn bull[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014he has majesty,and his horns
        are the horns of a wild ox;with them he shall gore the peoples,all of them,
        to the ends of the earth;  they are the ten thousands of Ephraim,and they
        are the thousands of Manasseh.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '33:17 '
        content: 'Dead Sea Scroll, Septuagint, Samaritan; Masoretic Text '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And of Zebulun he said,  \u201CRejoice, Zebulun, in your going out,and
        Issachar, in your tents.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "They shall call peoples to their mountain;there they offer right
        sacrifices;for they draw from the abundance of the seasand the hidden treasures
        of the sand.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And of Gad he said,\u201CBlessed be he who enlarges Gad!Gad crouches
        like a lion;he tears off arm and scalp.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "  He chose the best of the land for himself,for there a commander\u2019s
        portion was reserved;and he came with the heads of the people,with Israel
        he executed the justice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and his judgments
        for Israel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And of Dan he said,  \u201CDan is a lion\u2019s cub  that leaps from
        Bashan.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And of Naphtali he said,\u201CO Naphtali, sated with favor,and full
        of the blessing of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,  possess the lake[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and the south.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '33:23 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And of Asher he said,\u201CMost blessed of sons be Asher;let him
        be the favorite of his brothers,and let him dip his foot in oil.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Your bars shall be iron and bronze,and as your days, so shall your
        strength be.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "  \u201CThere is none like God, O Jeshurun,  who rides through the
        heavens to your help,through the skies in his majesty.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "The eternal God is your dwelling place,[[COMMENT(0)]]and underneath
        are the everlasting arms.And he thrust out the enemy before youand said,
        \u2018Destroy.\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '33:27 '
        content: 'Or Revocalization of verse 27 yields '
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So Israel lived in safety,  Jacob lived alone,[[COMMENT(0)]]in a
        land of grain and wine,whose heavens drop down dew.  '
      comments:
      - number: '33:28 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Happy are you, O Israel! Who is like you,a people saved by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, 
        the shield of your help,and the sword of your triumph!Your enemies shall
        come fawning to you,and you shall tread upon their backs.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Death of Moses'
      title: The Death of Moses
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Moses went up from the plains of Moab to Mount Nebo, to the
        top of Pisgah, which is opposite Jericho. And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        showed him all the land, Gilead as far as Dan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'all Naphtali, the land of Ephraim and Manasseh, all the land of Judah
        as far as the western sea, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'the Negeb, and the Plain, that is, the Valley of Jericho the city
        of palm trees, as far as Zoar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to him, \u201CThis is the
        land of which I swore to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob, \u2018I will give
        it to your offspring.\u2019 I have let you see it with your eyes, but you
        shall not go over there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So Moses the servant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> died there
        in the land of Moab, according to the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and he buried him in the valley in the land of Moab opposite Beth-peor;
        but no one knows the place of his burial to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Moses was 120 years old when he died. His eye was undimmed, and his
        vigor unabated. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the people of Israel wept for Moses in the plains of Moab thirty
        days. Then the days of weeping and mourning for Moses were ended.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And Joshua the son of Nun was full of the spirit of wisdom, for Moses
        had laid his hands on him. So the people of Israel obeyed him and did as
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had commanded Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And there has not arisen a prophet since in Israel like Moses, whom
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> knew face to face, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'none like him for all the signs and the wonders that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        sent him to do in the land of Egypt, to Pharaoh and to all his servants and
        to all his land, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: and for all the mighty power and all the great deeds of terror that
        Moses did in the sight of all Israel.
      comments: []
